column12: Flüssigkeitsfilter und Tankfiltersystem mit einem Flüssigkeitsfilter
column13: Die Erfindung betrifft einen Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) für ein Tankfiltersystem (100), wobei der Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) zum Einbau in einen Tank (101) geeignet ist. Der Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) weist ein Filtergehäuse (2) mit einem Zulauf (3) für eine Flüssigkeit (5) und mit einem Ablauf (4) für die Flüssigkeit (5) auf; er weist weiterhin auf einen hohlzylindrischen Filtereinsatz (10), der in einem Inneren (28) des Filtergehäuses (2) angeordnet ist und der eine erste Endkappe (11), eine zweite Endkappe (12) und ein in einer axialen Richtung (A) zwischen den beiden Endkappen (11, 12) angeordnetes Filtermedium (13) aufweist, wobei der Filtereinsatz (10) einen Innenraum (14) umschließt. Der Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) weist weiterhin auf ein Überdruckventil (6), welches bei Überschreiten eines definierten Drucks im Filtergehäuse (2) von einem geschlossenen Zustand in einen geöffneten Zustand überführt wird und dazu eingerichtet ist, im geöffneten Zustand Flüssigkeit (5) aus dem Inneren (28) des Filtergehäuses (2) in eine Außenumgebung (7) des Filtergehäuses (2) abzuführen, wobei das Überdruckventil (6) zumindest teilweise in den Innenraum (14) des Filtereinsatzes (10) hineinragt.
column15: ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS

column12: LIQUID FILTER AND VOLUME-EQUALIZING ELEMENT FOR A LIQUID FILTER
column13: The invention relates to a liquid filter. The liquid filter has a housing (2) with a cover (3) and also has an inflow (4) for a liquid and an outflow (5) for the liquid as well as a filter insert (20), which is arranged in an interior (6) of the housing (2) and has a first end cap (21), which is directed towards the cover (3), a second end cap (22) and a filter medium (23), which is arranged in an axial direction (A) between the two end caps (21, 22), wherein the filter insert (20) separates a clean side (7) from a dirty side (8). The liquid filter also has a volume-equalizing element (40) with a central body (41), which can be compressed in an elastically reversible manner and has a central-body interior space (42), wherein the central-body interior space (42), in a non-compressed state, encloses an initial volume and, in a compressed state, encloses an end volume, wherein the difference between the end volume and initial volume corresponds to at least 35% of a maximum change in volume of the liquid in the liquid filter (1) over a temperature range between +90° C and -40° C under normal pressure. The volume-equalizing element (40) here has a first sealing region (50), which surrounds the central body (41), wherein the first sealing region (50) is designed so that, when the liquid filter (1) is in the fully fitted state, said first sealing region interacts with the housing (2) and the cover (3) such that the interior (6) of the housing is sealed in a fluid-tight manner from an exterior space (9) of the liquid filter (1). The volume-equalizing element (40) here has a second sealing region (60), which surrounds the central body (41), wherein the second sealing region (60) is designed to prevent a fluidic short circuit between the clean side (7) and the dirty side (8).
column15: ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS

column12: Flüssigkeitsfilter und Volumenausgleichs-Element für einen Flüssigkeitsfilter
column13: Die Erfindung betrifft einen Flüssigkeitsfilter. Der Flüssigkeitsfilter weist ein Gehäuse (2) mit einem Deckel (3) auf sowie einen Zulauf (4) für eine Flüssigkeit und einen Ablauf (5) für die Flüssigkeit und einen Filtereinsatz (20), der in einem Inneren (6) des Gehäuses (2) angeordnet ist und der eine dem Deckel (3) zugewandte erste Endkappe (21), eine zweite Endkappe (22) und ein in einer axialen Richtung (A) zwischen den beiden Endkappen (21, 22) angeordnetes Filtermedium (23) aufweist, wobei der Filtereinsatz (20) eine Reinseite (7) von einer Rohseite (8) trennt. Er weist weiterhin ein Volumenausgleichs-Element (40) auf mit einem elastisch-reversibel komprimierbaren Zentralkörper (41), der einen Zentralkörper-Innenraum (42) aufweist, wobei der Zentralkörper-Innenraum (42) in einem nicht-komprimierten Zustand ein Anfangsvolumen umschließt und in einem komprimierten Zustand ein Endvolumen umschließt, wobei die Volumendifferenz zwischen Endvolumen und Anfangsvolumen zumindest 35% einer maximalen Volumenänderung der im Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) befindlichen Flüssigkeit im Temperaturbereich zwischen +90°C und - 40°C bei Normaldruck entspricht. Dabei weist das Volumenausgleichs-Element (40) einen den Zentralkörper (41) umlaufenden ersten Dichtungsbereich (50) auf, wobei der erste Dichtungsbereich (50) ausgebildet ist, im vollständig montierten Zustand des Flüssigkeitsfilters (1) mit dem Gehäuse (2) und dem Deckel (2) derart zusammenzuwirken, dass das Innere (6) des Gehäuses fluiddicht von einem Außenraum (9) des Flüssigkeitsfilters (1) abgedichtet ist. Dabei weist das Volumenausgleiches-Element (40) einen den Zentralkörper (41) umlaufenden zweiten Dichtungsbereich (60) aufweist, wobei der zweite Dichtungsbereich (60) ausgebildet ist, einen fluidischen Kurzschluss zwischen der Reinseite (7) und der Rohseite (8) zu verhindern.
column15: ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS

column12: Liquid filter and volume compensation element for liquid filter
column13: The invention relates to a liquid filter. The invention relates to a liquid filter having: a housing (2) comprising a cover (3); and a liquid inlet (4) and a liquid outlet (5); and a filter insert (20) which is arranged in the interior (6) of the housing (2) and has a first end shield (21) facing the cover (3), a second end shield (22) and a filter medium (23) which is arranged in the axial direction (A) between the two end shields (21, 22), the filter insert (20) separating the clean side (7) from the original side (8). Furthermore, the liquid filter has a volume compensation element (40) comprising an elastically reversibly compressible central body (41) having a central body interior (42), the central body interior (42) enclosing the initial volume in an uncompressed state and enclosing the final volume in a compressed state, the volume difference between the final volume and the initial volume corresponds to at least 35% of the maximum volume change of the liquid in the liquid filter (1) at normal pressure in a temperature range between + 90 DEG C and-40 DEG C. Here, the volume compensation element (40) has a first sealing region (50) surrounding the central body (41), the first sealing region (50) being designed to interact with the housing (2) and the cover part (2) in the fully assembled state of the liquid filter (1) such that the interior (6) of the housing is sealed in a fluid-tight manner from the exterior space (9) of the liquid filter (1). Here, the volume compensation element (40) has a second sealing region (60) surrounding the central body (41), the second sealing region (60) being designed to prevent a fluid short circuit between the clean side (7) and the original side (8).
column15: ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS

column13: A tourniquet may include an elastic band having a first end and a second end, a first attachment member affixed at the first end, a second attachment member affixed at the second end; and a third attachment member, which may be attached to and slideably displaceable along the elastic band. column12: Process for coating ferrous metal articles and resulting articles
column13: A process is described for thermo-chemically coating ferrous metal articles, especially small intricate ferrous articles. The process involves preparing a coating composition for homogenizing a complex of metal oxides and other solids in an organic liquid composition to obtain an emulsion, pre-heating the ferrous articles to an elevated temperature, immersing the pre-heated ferrous articles in the coating composition, withdrawing the articles and allowing them to cool.
column15: ARIAS JOSE V

column12: PKP Container
column13: De uitvinding is de PKP Container. De letters PKP staan voor Papier, Karton en Plastic. De PKP Container is speciaal ontworpen om afval beter en makkelijker te scheiden, met als doel vermindering van de huidige C02- uitstoot. Door het gebruik van de PKP Container wordt afval direct bij ieder huishouden en/of bedrijf gescheiden. De PKP Container is handzaam en eenvoudig plaatsbaar in elke (inbouw)keuken, bijkeuken, garage/schuur of werkplaats. De PKP Container scheidt en vermaalt automatisch en praktisch het afval direct na het deponeren. Het scheiden gaat automatisch door het ontwikkelde Plastic Recycling Codes en Logos Indentification Systeem (PRCIL Systeem) uniek en speciaal voor de PKP Container. Door betere scheiding en vermaling van het afval door de PKP Container zal de huidige inzamelingsfrequentie van afval afnemen. Door afname van de huidige inzamelingsfrequentie zullen ook de huidige bijkomende kosten van afvalverwerkingsbedrijven en gemeente afnemen en uiteindelijk heeft dit tot gevolg minder C02-uitstoot.
column15: JOSE NEPTALY ARIAS

column12: CONTAINER
column13: The present invention relates to a container for shredding packaging materials, provided with a camera, a shredder with a funnel, a number of waste units and an identification system for recognizing recycling codes on plastic packaging materials and recycling logos on beverage cartons and metal packagings, such as tin and aluminium. The identification system is configured to perform the following steps of: a) scanning or making a recording of a recycling code or recycling logo on packaging material by means of the camera; b) recognizing the recycling code or the recycling logo; c) automatically placing a waste unit for the recognized recycling code or the recognized recycling logo under the funnel of the shredder.

column12: CONTAINER
column13: De onderhavige uitvinding betreft een container voor het vermalen van verpakkingsmaterialen, voorzien van een camera, een shredder met een trechter, een aantal afvalunits en een identificatiesysteem voor het herkennen van recyclingcodes op plastic verpakkingsmaterialen en recycling logo's op drankenkartons en metalen verpakkingen, zoals blik, en aluminium. Het identificatiesysteem is ingericht voor het uitvoeren van de volgende stappen: a) het middels de camera scannen of het maken van een opname van een recyclingcode of recycling logo op verpakkingsmateriaal; b) het herkennen van de recyclingcode of het recycling logo; c) het automatisch plaatsen van een afvalunit voor de herkende recyclingcode of het herkende recycling logo onder de trechter van de shredder.

column12: Removal tool for a filter insert of a liquid filter
column13: A removal tool for a filter insert of a liquid filter. The removal tool includes a first arm having a first outer side, the first outer side extending along a first axis. It furthermore includes a second arm having a second outer side, the second outer side extending along a second axis. The first arm includes a first hook, which projects from the first arm essentially transversely to the first axis. The second arm includes a second hook, which projects from the second arm essentially transversely to the second axis. The first outer side and the second outer side are connected to one another with a swivel joint having a joint axis.
column15: BALLESTE IZUZQUIZA ELENA;;ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS

column12: Tiltermodul
column13: Die vorliegende Erfindung betrifft ein Filtermodul (1) zum Filtern eines Fluides, wobei das Filtermodul (1) eine ungefilterte Seite (2), über die ein Fluid eingebbar ist, und eine gefilterte Seite (3), über die ein Fluid ausgebbar ist, aufweist, wobei zwischen der ungefilterten Seite (2) und der gefilterten Seite (3) ein Filterelement (4) angeordnet ist, wobei zwischen der gefilterten Seite (3) und dem Filterelement (4) ein Deckelelement (9) mit einem Fluiddurchlass (21) angeordnet ist, wobei das Deckelelement (9) einen Bypass (5) aufweist, der zur Umgehung des Filterelements (4) die ungefilterte Seite (2) und die gefilterte Seite (3) verbindet, wobei ein erstes Rückschlagventil (6) einen Fluidfluss durch den Fluiddurchlass (21) von der gefilterten Seite zu dem Filterelement (4) verhindert, und wobei ein zweites Rückschlagventil (7) einen Fluidfluss von der ungefilterten Seite (2) zu der gefilterten Seite (3) durch den Bypass (5) verhindert.
column15: CASTEJON LOPEZ MIGUEL;;ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS

column12: Filtereinsatz und Flüssigkeitsfilter mit einem derartigen Filtereinsatz
column13: Die Erfindung betrifft einen Filtereinsatz (20) für einen Flüssigkeitsfilter (1), der Filtereinsatz (20) aufweisend:-- eine erste Endkappe (21);-- eine zweite Endkappe (22);--ein in einer axialen Richtung (A) zwischen den beiden Endkappen (21, 22) angeordnetes Filtermedium (23);wobei die erste Endkappe (21) exzentrisch zu einer Längsachse (LA) eine Befestigungsstruktur (28) aufweist, mittels derer der Filtereinsatz (20) im Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) lösbar befestigbar ist.
column15: ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS;;GARCIA JAVIER FERNANDEZ

column12: REMOVAL TOOL FOR A FILTER INSERT OF A LIQUID FILTER
column13: The invention relates to a removal tool (1) for a filter insert (70) of a liquid filter (90). The removal tool (1) comprises a body (2) which extends along a longitudinal axis (A). The body (2) has a first arm (10) and a second arm (20) on a distal end (3), wherein the two arms (10, 20) extend substantially parallel to the longitudinal axis (A) and are spaced apart from one another. The two arms (10, 20) can be resiliently reversibly deflected towards one another. A securing element (30, 32) is arranged on the first arm (10). In an open state (50) of the securing element (30) the two arms (10, 20) can be moved towards one another. In a closed state (52) of the securing element (30, 32), the securing element (30, 32) couples the two arms (10, 20) to one another and blocks a movement of the two arms (10, 20) towards one another.
column15: ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS;;BALLESTE IZUZQUIZA ELENA

column12: REMOVAL TOOL FOR A FILTER INSERT OF A LIQUID FILTER
column13: The invention relates to a removal tool (1) for a filter insert (70) of a liquid filter (90). The removal tool (1) according to the invention comprises a first arm (10) having a first outer side (13),wherein the first outer side (13) extends along a first axis (A1). The removal tool furthermore comprises a second arm (20) having a second outer side (23), wherein the second outer side (23) extendsalong a second axis (A2). The first arm (10) has a first hook (11), which protrudes substantially transverse to the first axis (A1) of the first arm (10). The second arm (20) has a second hook (21),which protrudes substantially transverse to the second axis (A2) of the second arm (20). According to the invention, the first outer side (13) and the second outer side (23) are connected to each other by means of a swivel joint (30, 32) having a joint axis (A3).
column15: ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS;;BALLESTE IZUZQUIZA ELENA

column12: REMOVAL TOOL FOR A FILTER INSERT OF A LIQUID FILTER
column13: A removal tool for a filter insert of a liquid filter. The removal tool includes a body extending along a longitudinal axis. At a distal end, the body includes a first arm and a second arm, the two arms extending essentially in parallel to the longitudinal axis and being spaced apart from one another. The two arms are elastically reversibly deflectable toward one another. A retaining element is situated at the first arm. In an open state of the retaining element, the two arms may be moved toward one another. In a closed state of the retaining element, the retaining element couples the two arms to one another and blocks a movement of the two arms toward one another.

column12: Flüssigkeitsfilter und Filtereinsatz für einen Flüssigkeitsfilter
column13: Die Erfindung betrifft einen Flüssigkeitsfilter (1), wobei der Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) ein Gehäuse (2) aufweist mit einem Innenraum (3), der sich entlang einer Achse (A) erstreckt. Der Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) weist weiterhin auf: einen Zulauf (4) für eine Flüssigkeit, einen Ablauf (5) für die Flüssigkeit und einen Filtereinsatz (6), der in den Innenraum (3) einsteckbar ist. Der Filtereinsatz (6) ist im Innenraum (3) des Gehäuses (2) angeordnet. Der Filtereinsatz (6) weist ein erstes Filterelement (10) mit einem ersten Filtermedium (11) auf, wobei das erste Filtermedium (11) eine erste Rohseite (12) von einer ersten Reinseite (13) trennt,wobei das erste Filtermedium (11) zur Grobfiltrierung eingerichtet ist. Der Filtereinsatz (6) weist ein zweites Filterelement (20) mit einem zweiten Filtermedium (21) auf, wobei das zweite Filtermedium (21) eine zweite Rohseite (22) von einer zweiten Reinseite (23) trennt, wobei das zweite Filtermedium (21) zur Feinfiltrierung eingerichtet ist. Das zweite Filterelement (20) ist im Normalbetrieb fluidisch dem ersten Filterelement (10) nachgeschaltet, wobei das erste Filterelement (10) und das zweite Filterelement (20) in axialer Richtung hintereinander angeordnet sind,wobei in axialer Richtung betrachtet zwischen dem ersten Filterelement (10) und dem zweiten Filterelement (20) ein Trennelement (50) vorgesehen ist, welches die erste Reinseite (13) von der zweiten Rohseite (22) fluiddicht abdichtet, wobei das Gehäuse (2) einen ersten Anschluss (8) aufweist, der eingerichtet ist, die erste Reinseite (13) mit einem Pumpenzulauf (41) einer Pumpe (40) fluidleitend zu verbinden, wobei das Gehäuse (2) einen zweiten Anschluss (9) aufweist, der eingerichtet ist, die zweite Rohseite (22) mit einem Pumpenablauf (42) der Pumpe (40) fluidleitend zu verbinden.
column15: ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS;;GARCIA JAVIER FERNANDEZ

Le premier bras (10) a un premier crochet (11) en saillie transversalement au premier axe (A1) et le second bras (20) a un second crochet (21) en saillie transversalement au second axe (A2). column12: FILTER INSERT AND LIQUID FILTER COMPRISING SUCH A FILTER INSERT
column13: The invention relates to a filter insert (20) for a fluid filter (1), the filter insert (20) comprising: - a first end cap (21); - a second end cap (22); - a filter medium (23) arranged between both end caps (21, 22) in an axial direction (A); wherein the first end cap (21) has a fastening structure eccentrically to a longitudinal axis (LA), by means of which the filter insert (20) is removably fastenable in the fluid filter (1).

column12: Demontagewerkzeug für einen Filtereinsatz eines Flüssigkeitsfilters
column13: Die Erfindung betrifft ein Demontagewerkzeug (1) für einen Filtereinsatz (70) eines Flüssigkeitsfilters (90). Das Demontagewerkzeug (1) umfasst einen ersten Arm (10) mit einer ersten Außenseite (13), wobei sich die erste Außenseite (13) entlang einer ersten Achse (A1) erstreckt. Es umfasst weiterhin einen zweiten Arm (20) mit einer zweiten Außenseite (23), wobei sich die zweite Außenseite (23) entlang einer zweiten Achse (A2) erstreckt. Der erste Arm (10) weist einen ersten Haken (11) auf, der im Wesentlichen quer zur ersten Achse (A1) vom ersten Arm (10) abragt. Der zweite Arm (20) weist einen zweiten Haken (21) auf, der im Wesentlichen quer zur zweiten Achse (A2) vom zweiten Arm (20) abragt. Dabei sind die erste Außenseite (13) und die zweite Außenseite (23) mittels eines Drehgelenks (30, 32) mit einer Gelenkachse (A3) miteinander verbunden.
column15: BALLESTE IZUZQUIZA ELENA;;ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS

column12: Demontagewerkzeug für einen Filtereinsatz eines Flüssigkeitsfilters
column13: Die Erfindung betrifft ein Demontagewerkzeug (1) für einen Filtereinsatz (70) eines Flüssigkeitsfilters (90). Das Demontagewerkzeug (1) umfasst einen Körper (2), der sich entlang einer Längsachse (A) erstreckt. Der Körper (2) weist an einem distalen Ende (3) einen ersten Arm (10) und einen zweiten Arm (20) auf, wobei sich die beiden Arme (10, 20) im Wesentlichen parallel zur Längsachse (A) erstrecken und voneinander beabstandet sind. Die beiden Arme (10, 20) sind elastisch reversibel aufeinander zu auslenkbar. Dabei ist vorgesehen, dass am ersten Arm (10) ein Sicherungselement (30, 32) angeordnet ist. Dabei können in einem geöffneten Zustand (50) des Sicherungselements (30) die beiden Arme (10, 20) aufeinander zu bewegt werden. In einem geschlossenen Zustand (52) des Sicherungselements (30, 32) koppelt das Sicherungselement (30, 32) die beiden Arme (10, 20) miteinander und blockiert eine Bewegung der beiden Arme (10, 20) aufeinander zu.
column15: BALLESTE IZUZQUIZA ELENA;;ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS

column12: Filter module
column13: The invention relates to a filter module (1) used for filtering fluids. The filter module (1) comprises an un-filtered side portion (2) and a filtered side portion (3). The un-filtered side portion enables fluids to be input, and the filtered side portion enables fluids to be output. A filter component (4) is arranged between the un-filtered side portion (2) and the filtered side portion (3). A cover member (9) with a fluid penetrating part (21) is arranged between the filtered side portion (3) and the filter component (4). The cover member (9) has a bypass portion (5). To detour from the filter component (4), the bypass portion connects the un-filtered side portion (2) with the filtered side portion (3). A first check valve (6) prevents fluids from flowing from the filtered side portion to the filter component (4) through the fluid penetrating part (21). A second check valve (7) prevents fluids from flowing from the un-filtered side portion (2) to the filtered side portion (3) through the bypass portion (5).
column15: MIGUEL CASTEJON LOPEZ;;JOSE LUIS ARIAS ARIAS

column12: ANTIHYPERTENSION TREATMENT
column13: -a- The present specification discloses a class of chemical compounds the members of which when introduced by ingestion, injection, absorption, or otherwise into a mammal (including man), produce avoidance, amelioration and/or inprovement of a hypertensive conditon in mammals and man when used in an antihypertensively effective amount as taught herein. The active antihypertensive agents used in the compositions of the present invention fall into four broad categories. They are: (1) the inorganic salts of sulfurous acid which display antihypertensive activity, specifically the alkali metal, alkaline earth metal, and ammonium salts of sulfites and bisulfites (including metabisulfites) and mixtures thereof. Alkali metal, particularly sodium and potassium bisulfites are preferred active agents, and, of these, sodium bisulfite is a presently most preferred active agent. Also, because of similar toxicological considerations, the calcium, magnesium, and ammonium compounds are also preferred. (2) A compound of the formula: in which R is hydrogen or hydroxymethyl, R1 is hydrogen, a straight chain alkyl containing 2 to 5 hydroxylated carbon atoms, or residue of a polysaccharide capable of reducing Fehling's solution, while X is an alkali metal or ammonium. Illustrative compounds include sodium glucose bisulfite and sodium formaldehyde bisulfite. (3) A lower alkyl amine sulfite compound of the formula: - b where R1 is lower alkyl, cycloalkly containing from 6 to 10 carbon atoms each, lower monohydroxyalkyl or aralkyl, R2 is hydrogen, lower alkyl or lower monohydroxyalkyl, or R1 and R2 together constitute a morpholine, piperidine, or hexamethyleneimine ring, provided that each such ring can be substituted on one of its carbon atoms by lower alkyl radical, R3 is lower aalkyl, lower monohydroxyalkyl, hydrogen, or a compound of the formula: in which R4 is a divalent saturated lower aliphatic radical, m and n are intergers, the sum of m and n is 2, and n is eithr 0 or 1.

column12: Removal tool for a filter insert of a liquid filter
column13: A removal tool for a filter insert of a liquid filter. The removal tool includes a body extending along a longitudinal axis. At a distal end, the body includes a first arm and a second arm, the two arms extending essentially in parallel to the longitudinal axis and being spaced apart from one another. The two arms are elastically reversibly deflectable toward one another. A retaining element is situated at the first arm. In an open state of the retaining element, the two arms may be moved toward one another. In a closed state of the retaining element, the retaining element couples the two arms to one another and blocks a movement of the two arms toward one another.

column12: NUEVA PASTA PARA MOLDEAR Y RECREAR
column13: Pasta de moldeo obtenida mediante un procedimiento de mezclado y agitación a temperaturas controlables, de una serie de ingredientes que en su orden son: un polímetro polar, agua, agentes de relleno, espesantes acuosos, agentes de gelación, plastificantes, suavizantes, humectantes, colorantes, fragancias, lubricantes, preservativos y oleato - estearato de sodio.Pasta de moldeo según la reivindicación 1 en la cual la composición de los polímero polar, 25 a 50% de agentes de relleno, 25 a 45% de humectantes, 5 a16% de oleato de estearato de sodio, 1 a 2% de agentes de gelación, 1 a 5% de espesantes 1 a 2% de lubricantes, 1 a 5% de colorantes, 0.1 a 2% de plastificantes, 0.1 a 2% de fragancias y 0.1 a 2% de preservativos.Pasta de moldeo según las reivindicaciones 1 y 2 en donde el polímero polar es un alcohol polivinilico con un peso molecular entre 10.000 y 200.000 y un grado de hidrólisis mayor que el 80%.Pasta de moldeo según las reivindicaciones 1 y 2 en la cual el agente de gelación se escoge del grupo del ácido bórico, entre el bórax, el borato de sodio, el zinc y compuestos del zirconico.Pastas según las reivindicaciones 1 y 2 en el cual los agentes de rellenos se escogen entre el caolín, la mica, la arcilla, el talco, el carbonato de calcio y el silicato de aluminio preferiblemente.Pasta según las reivindicaciones 1 y 2 en donde el plastificante es un oleato - estearato de sodio en proporción de 40 a 80% de oleato y de 20 a 60% de estearato.Pasta según las reivindicaciones 1 y 2 en donde los espesantes incluyen derivados de celulosa como el hidroxietil celulosa, el hidroxipropil celulosa y el carboximetil celulosa, preferiblemente.Pasta según las reivindicaciones 1 y 2 en donde los espesantes incluyen además almidones, gomas, jabones de sodio y espesantes acrílicos.Pasta según las reivindicaciones 1 y 2 en donde los lubricantes son del orden de aceites vegetales, aceites minerales y parafina preferiblemente.

column12: ECOLOGICAL FORMULA HAVING MULTIPLE ANTIMICROBIAL ACTION (BACTERICIDAL, FUNGICIDAL AND ANTI-VIRAL) BASED ON COMMERCIAL MOLECULES
column13: The invention relates to the application of a formula for controlling pests of microbial origin by combining hydrogen peroxide, 2-hydroxy-1,2,3-tricarboxylic acid and water treated as a solvent, generating a method for controlling pests of microbial origin, the formula having biocidal and disinfectant activity on a complex range of microorganisms such as bacteria, fungi, yeasts, endospores and viruses and killing Gram-positive bacteria, Gram-negative bacteria, microbacteria, Staphylococcus aureus, Streptococcus mutans and Candida albicans. The effects of the formula are lethal for microorganisms with aerobic metabolism or anaerobic metabolism, with very positive effects in citrus fruit plantations with citrus greening disease (HLB) and cocoa plantations, with organic certification for exportation, which are affected by fungi, and for any other disease of microbial origin affecting harvests of fruits and vegetables. The formula can also be used for the treatment of vegetables for exportation with organic certification. In addition, microbial diseases in animals and humans can be treated and cured with this formula. The formula can be used for hygiene on surfaces, by means of cleaning products, paint formulas, cosmetics, beauty products, home economy materials, and as an antimicrobial additive for extending the shelf life of products.

column12: Device for pumping fuel
column13: Devices are known for pumping fuel out of a fuel tank to an internal combustion engine. These devices comprise a tank flange for closing an opening of the fuel tank, said tank flange having a receiving area in which a filter housing is secured in a form-fitting and/or force-fitting manner. The filter housing has a hydraulic connection at one of the two end faces of the filter housing and is made of plastic. The filter housing can be released and removed from the receiving area of the tank flange by rotating the filter housing. The filter housing is difficult to replace for garage personnel because the tank flange with the receiving area for the filter housing is arranged on a fuel tank upper face which is frequently only poorly accessible. The device according to the invention simplifies the replacement of the filter housing. According to the invention, two opposing lateral surfaces (11) are provided on an outer contour of the hydraulic connection (10), said lateral surfaces being arranged parallel to each other and forming a tool attachment.
column15: ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS;;BALAZ JAN;;PTACEK MARTIN

column12: Vorrichtung zum Fördern von Kraftstoff
column13: Es sind schon Vorrichtungen zum Fördern von Kraftstoff aus einem Kraftstofftank zu einer Brennkraftmaschine bekannt. Diese Vorrichtungen umfassen einen Tankflansch zum Verschließen einer Öffnung des Kraftstofftanks, wobei der Tankflansch eine Aufnahme aufweist, in der ein Filtergehäuse form- und/oder kraftschlüssig befestigt ist. Das Filtergehäuse weist an einer seiner beiden Stirnseiten einen hydraulischen Anschluss auf und ist aus Kunststoff hergestellt. Das Filtergehäuse kann durch eine Drehbewegung des Filtergehäuses gelöst und aus der Aufnahme des Tankflansches herausgenommen werden. Der Austausch des Filtergehäuses ist für Werkstattpersonal schwierig, das der Tankflansch mit der Aufnahme für das Filtergehäuse an einer Oberseite des Kraftstofftanks angeordnet ist, die häufig nur schwer zugänglich ist. Bei der erfindungsgemäßen Vorrichtung wird der Austausch des Filtergehäuses vereinfacht. Erfindungsgemäß ist vorgesehen, dass an einer Außenkontur des hydraulischen Anschlusses (10) zwei sich gegenüberliegende Seitenflächen (11) vorgesehen sind, die parallel zueinander angeordnet sind und einen Werkzeugansatz bilden.
column15: BALAZ JAN;;ARIAS ARIAS JOSE LUIS;;PTACEK MARTIN

column12: Vorrichtung zum Fördern von Kraftstoff
column13: Es sind schon Vorrichtungen zum Fördern von Kraftstoff aus einem Kraftstofftank zu einer Brennkraftmaschine bekannt, mit einem Tankflansch zum Verschließen einer Öffnung des Kraftstofftanks, wobei der Tankflansch eine Aufnahme für ein austauschbares Filtergehäuse aufweist, in der das Filtergehäuse angeordnet ist. Das Filtergehäuse weist ein erstes Gehäuseteil und ein mit dem ersten Gehäuseteil verbundenes zweites Gehäuseteil auf, wobei das Filtergehäuse über Befestigungsmittel in der Aufnahme gehalten ist. Am Umfang des Filtergehäuses ist ein Dichtmittel vorgesehen, das einen Ringspalt zwischen der Aufnahme und dem Filtergehäuse abdichtet. Das erste Gehäuseteil und das zweite Gehäuseteil sind miteinander verschweißt. Wenn das Filtergehäuse in der Aufnahme des Tankflansches montiert ist, liegt die Fügeverbindung zwischen den beiden Gehäuseteilen des Filtergehäuses außerhalb des Kraftstofftanks, so dass Kraftstoff bei undichter Fügeverbindung aus dem Filtergehäuse nach außerhalb des Kraftstoffsystems und nach außerhalb des Kraftstofftanks gelangen kann. Bei der erfindungsgemäßen Vorrichtung kann kein Kraftstoff bei undichter Fügeverbindung zwischen den beiden Gehäuseteilen aus dem Kraftstoffsystem entweichen. Erfindungsgemäß ist vorgesehen, dass das erste Gehäuseteil (6.1) in die Aufnahme (5) des Tankflansches (3) hineinragt und das Dichtmittel (11) an dem ersten Gehäuseteil (6.1) vorgesehen ist.

column12: dispositivo para o bombeamento de combustível
column13: a presente invenção refere-se a conhecidos dispositivos para o bombeamento de combustível de um tanque de combustível até um motor de combustão interna. estes dispositivos compreendem um flange de tanque para o fechamento de uma abertura do tanque de combustível, onde o flange de tanque apresenta um assento, onde é fixada uma caixa de filtro com fecho devido à forma e/ou com fecho devido à força. a caixa de filtro possui em um dos seus dois lados frontais uma conexão hidráulica e é feita de material sintético. a caixa de filtro pode ser solta por meio de um movimento de rotação da caixa de filtro e ser retirada do assento do flange de tanque. a substituição da caixa de filtro é complicada para o pessoal das oficinas, uma vez que o flange de tanque com o assento para a caixa de filtro é disposto em um lado superior do tanque de combustível frequentemente é de difícil acesso. no caso do dispositivo de acordo com a presente invenção, a substituição da caixa de filtro é simplificada. de acordo com a presente invenção é previsto que em um contorno externo da conexão hidráulica (10) são previstas duas faces laterais (11) mutuamente opostas que estão dispostas paralelamente uma com a outra, constituindo uma saliência para a ferramenta.
column15: JAN BALAZ;;JOSE LUIS ARIAS ARIAS;;MARTIN PTACEK

column12: Device for conveying fuel
column13: The invention relates to a device for conveying fuel from a fuel tank (1) to an internal combustion engine (2), comprising a tank flange (3) for closing an opening (4) of the fuel tank (1), wherein the tank flange (3) has a mount (5) for an exchangeable filter housing (6), and comprising a filter housing (6), which is arranged in the mount (5) of the tank flange (3) and which has a first housing part (6.1) and a second housing part (6.2) connected to the first housing part (6.1), wherein the first housing part (6.1) protrudes into the mount (5) of the tank flange (3) and a sealing means (11) is provided on the first housing part (6.1). In the case of the device according to the invention, fuel cannot escape from the fuel system if the joint between the two housing parts is not tight.

column12: LEITFÄHIGE ELEMENTE MIT UNVERSPERRTEM GRENZFLÄCHENBEREICH FÜR DIE-ANBRINGUNG IN FLIP-CHIP-GEHÄUSEN
column13: Ein Halbleitergehäuse beinhaltet einen Halbleiter-Die mit einer Vorrichtungsseite, eine leitfähige Schicht, die mit der Vorrichtungsseite gekoppelt ist, eine leitfähige Säule, die mit der leitfähigen Schicht gekoppelt ist, wobei die leitfähige Säule einen oberen Teil und einen Basisteil aufweist, wobei der obere Teil einen breiteren Durchmesser als der Basisteil aufweist und die leitfähige Säule entweder eine Pilzform aufweist oder geneigte Seiten auf dem Basisteil aufweist, die sich von dem oberen Teil weg zu der leitfähigen Schicht erstrecken, eine Polyimidschicht, die mit der leitfähigen Schicht gekoppelt ist und die die leitfähige Säule umgibt, eine Lotschicht, die mit der leitfähigen Säule gekoppelt ist, wobei sich die Polyimidschicht nicht zwischen einer oberen Oberfläche der leitfähigen Säule und der Lotschicht erstreckt, und einen leitfähigen Anschluss, der mit der Lotschicht gekoppelt ist und auf einer Oberfläche des Halbleitergehäuses freigelegt ist, wobei die Vorrichtungsseite des Halbleiter-Die dem leitfähigen Anschluss zugewandt ist.

column12: Flüssigkeitsfilter und Tankfiltersystem mit einem Flüssigkeitsfilter
column13: Die Erfindung betrifft einen Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) zum Abscheiden von Partikeln aus einer Flüssigkeit, insbesondere aus Kraftstoff oder einer Harnstofflösung. Der Flüssigkeitsfilter (1) weist ein erstes Filtermedium (10), ein zweites Filtermedium (20) und einen Tragrahmen (2) mit einer Tragrahmenwand (3) auf. Die Tragrahmenwand (3) weist eine erste Stirnseite (4) und eine davon abgewandte zweite Stirnseite (5) auf. Das erste Filtermedium (10) ist auf der ersten Stirnseite (4) fluiddicht befestigt und das zweite Filtermedium (20) ist auf der zweiten Stirnseite (5) fluiddicht befestigt. Der Tragrahmen (2), das erste Filtermedium (10) und das zweite Filtermedium (20) umschließen einen Innenraum (7). Das erste Filtermedium (10) weist eine erste Durchgangsöffnung (12) auf, wobei im Innenraum (7) ein erstes Filterelement (50) angeordnet ist, welches fluidleitend mit der ersten Durchgangsöffnung (12) verbunden ist. Die Erfindung betrifft weiterhin ein Tankfiltersystem (100) mit einem derartigen Flüssigkeitsfilter (1).

column12: TIRA CONECTORA DE TERMINALES Y PROCESO PARA SELLARLA
column13: Una tira conectora 1 provista con una serie de compartimentos o cámaras 2 para sendos terminales 3 en los cuales se insertan hilos conductores 8 por medio de una herramienta de instalación a fin de establecer conexión entre los terminales y los hilos conductores desplazando la aislación de éstos. Cada cámara 2 es independiente de las cámaras adyacentes, estando separadas por medio de particiones transversales 4, 4´ que permiten verter un gel o producto sellador dentro de la respectiva cámara 2 hasta un nivel 12 que es inferior al del escalón de entrada 10 de los hilos conductores 8 y está encima del borde de los terminales 3 a fin de que tanto dichos terminales como las conexiones de los mismos con los conductores 8 estén sumergidos en el producto sellador para impedir la oxidación de las conexiones

column12: Multi-terminal connector strip and procedure for the sealing thereof
column13: The strip (1) is provided with a series of housings (2) for a like number of terminals (3) to which conductor wires (8) accede thrust by a tool (11) in order to establish connection, by means of displacing the conductor wires (8) over the terminals (3). Each housing or chamber (2) is independent of those adjacent, the separation being constituted by means of transversal partitions (4) and (4'), which makes possible the pouring of a sealing gel into the respective housing chamber (2) up to a level (12) which is at a height lower than the entrance step (10) of the conductor wires (8) and above the edge of the terminals (3), with the objective that both said terminals and the connections thereof with the conductors (8) be immersed in the sealing gel in order to prevent oxidation on the connections.

column12: TORTILLA MAKING STAMPER MACHINE.
column13: The present invention discloses a tortilla making stamper machine comprising four rollers manufactured or coated from diverse materials that allow the adherence thereof with the corn dough to be controlled, the stamper machine being characterized in that it comprises a synchronized rotary movement of the rollers relative to each other so that the dough is automatically conveyed into the rollers and subsequently shaped as a thin layer that remains adhered to one of the rollers, a cylindrical die operating thereon and thereby providing the dough layer with the final tortilla shape. The tortillas thus formed are stuck to the last roller and transferred to a conveying belt by the action of a drive roller. The machine also includes a manually or automatically adjustable die ensuring that the tortillas are produced with a perfect geometry.

column12: DEPOLYMERIZATION

column12: TORTILLA-PROCESSING MACHINE BY A PRESSING METHOD.
column13: The present invention discloses a plurality of modular devices that allow tortillas to be produced on industrial scale with a maximum efficiency and the ability to reproduce the quality, texture and appearance of the best handmade tortillas as standardized as possible. In order to achieve this, a completely modular electromechanical design has been employed for manufacturing Testal or dough-ball pressing units (the dough in the process of making tortillas before it is cooked) for different types of dough, the basic pressing unit comprising a mechanical press impelled by a direct current motor which is controlled by an electronic unit for monitoring the general operation of the press. The control circuit indirectly determines when the compression plate has collided with stopping elements that define the tortilla thickness by means of the current drawn by the motor. Because the stopping elements are manually placed on the machine base and may be adjusted to a predetermined thickness, t hey may also be integral with a fully automatic system which is controlled by the electronic control unit, thereby allowing the machine to produce tortillas having different thicknesses which are determined by an electronic command, this feature being of decisive importance as the taste, texture and appearance of tortillas greatly depend on the Testal thickness used for the manufacture thereof. The pressing system is enhanced by using a plurality of tools that facilitate the Testal detachment from the compression plate, said tools being interchangeable and operating over the core design of the press structure. The tools of the invention include the use of contact plates providing a lotus-type effect, this effect being named after the Egyptian lotus properties which is repellent to almost everything, and when compared with the Lotus effect, Teflon is a mediocre-quality anti-adherent. The lotus-effect compression plate is manufactured by deposition of nanoparticles on the surface of a plurality of materials by a chemical process which allows an anti-adherent pressure surface to be obtained. The invention also includes the use of compression plates cooled by peltier-type electronic coolers in order to take advantage of the fact that adherence is often directly proportional to temperature, so that there is proposed a design wherein the compression plate is cooled and automatically maintained at about two degrees above the freezing point. In an alternate embodiment of the invention, there is provided an accessory method for our compression tortilla-making design, which comprises using electrostatic charges for controlling the Testal adhesion to each of the first and second compression plates. There is still further provided a method for compressing the Testal by means of a spherical-shaped element made of flexible material which exerts pressure on the Testal when inflated, thereby flattening the same on a plate to obtain a raw tortilla in its traditional shape. The inflation and disinflation process of the spherical-shaped element is performed by displacement of a piston within a cylinder which transfers fluid from the inner portion thereof to the inner portion of the spherical-shaped element, this design being substantially simple and efficient and enables high speed production of tortillas. In addition to the compression unit, there is further disclosed a volume-conveying auger design, the augers being manufactured by polymer injection, thereby obtaining augers with higher efficiency and hygiene features than those made of welded metal. The design of the augers is made so that its removal from molds is feasible as not every auger geometry design may be manufactured by the injection method due to the angles that are generated during the process by the curved surface. For the purpose of the present invention, the augers are molded on a steel shaft, which ensures a perfect and permanent attachment to be obtained therebetween, and allowing the augers to be used for compressing the dough and preparing the same for the Testal-shaping process. These augers are also integral with the design of the dispensing machine module which produces the Testal with the weight and form required by using a cylindrical-shaped element wherein an auger is forcibly disposed therein and driven by a stepper motor, this motor rotating a predetermined number of degrees as commanded by the electronic control unit thereof, thereby resulting in a perfectly predetermined displacement of the dough inside the cylindrical-shaped element. A trimming plate is useful for separating the Testal to be processed from the remaining dough, and an optoelectronic assembly serves as an additional element for controlling the Testal volume, said optoelectronic assembly comprising a light transmitter and a light receiver which may be collimated so that the assembly serves as a displacement detector for preventing the Testal from exceeding a predetermined size.

column12: INSTALACOES E LIGACOES DE FILTROS DE BANDA LARGA

column12: MULTI-TERMINAL CONNECTOR STRIP AND PROCEDURE FOR THE SEALING THEREOF
column13: The strip (1) is provided with a series of housings (2) for a like number of terminals (3) to which conductor wires (8) accede thrust by a tool (11) in order to establish connection, by means of displacing the conductor wires (8) over the terminals (3). Each housing or chamber (2) is independent of those adjacent, the separation being constituted by means of transversal partitions (4) and (4'), which makes possible the pouring of a sealing gel into the respective housing chamber (2) up to a level (12) which is at a height lower than the entrance step (10) of the conductor wires (8) and above the edge of the terminals (3), with the objective that both said terminals and the connections thereof with the conductors (8) be immersed in the sealing gel in order to prevent oxidation on the connections.

column12: ARQUITECTURA DE CONEXION PARA REDES XDSL Y MARCO DE DISTRIBUCION INTERMEDIO REQUERIDO POR DICHA ARQUITECTURA
column13: La arquitectura de conexión permite monitorear digitalmente los filtros, conectando directamente la mesa de pruebas al marco de distribución intermedio sin requerir cableado al DSLAM, de manera que en dicho marco de distribución intermedio pueden colocarse las tarjetas de filtro de los operadores dominantes y de segundos operadores, al menos una tarjeta inteligente que contiene los relays que son activados desde la mesa de pruebas, para lo cual se utiliza un canal (bus) digital, permitiendo medir el circuito de suscriptor para filtros de segundos operadores y también la senal de DSLAM para el operador dominante. Se provee además una tarjeta adicional cuyo objeto es recibir y distribuir la senal que llega desde el DSLAM entre los filtros, y conectores a los cuales se conectan las tarjetas de filtro de manera que cuando las tarjetas son extraídas, la entrada (voz) esté conectada a la salida (voz más datos) y así la senal de voz no se interrumpa.

column12: TIRA CONECTORA DE TERMINALES MULTIPLES Y PROCESO PARA SELLARLA
column13: DONDE LA TIRA COMPRENDE UN CUERPO ALARGADO QUE INCORPORA UNA SERIE DE CAMARAS PARA SENDOS TERMINALES A LOS CUALES PUEDEN CONECTARSE HILOS CONDUCTORES EMPUJANDOLOS DENTRO DE LAS CAMARAS POR MEDIO DE UNA HERRAMIENTA APROPIADA, CON LO CUAL LOS HILOS CONDUCTORES SON INSERTADOS DENTRO DE RANURAS PROVISTAS EN LOS TERMINALES QUE CORTAN LA AISLACION DE LOS HILOS CONDUCTORES A FIN DE ESTABLECER CONEXION ELECTRICA ENTRE ESTOS Y LOS TERMINALES, DONDE LA CAMARA PARA CADA PAR DE TERMINALES ESTA SEPARADA DE CADA CAMARA ADYACENTE POR MEDIO DE RESPECTIVAS PARTICIONES TRANSVERSALES, DE MANERA DE PERMITIR VERTER UN PRODUCTO SELLADOR EN CADA UNA DE LAS CAMARAS A FIN DE PROTEGER LOS HILOS CONDUCTORES. EL PROCESO INCLUYE VERTER DENTRO DE LAS CAMARAS UN GEL O PRODUCTO SELLADOR ADECUADO HASTA QUE SE ALCANCE UN NIVEL POR ENCIMA DEL BORDE SUPERIOR DE LOS TERMINALES, Y POR DEBAJO DEL BORDE DEFINIDO POR EL ESCALON SUPERIOR DE ENTRADA DE LOS HILOS CONDUCTORES CORRESPONDIENTE A LOS BORDES LATERALES DE LA TIRA; SECAR O CURAR EL PRODUCTO SELLADOR DESPUES DEL VERTIDO; Y, EFECTUAR LA CONEXION ENTRE LOS TERMINALES Y LOS HILOS CONDUCTORES

column12: Tira conectora de múltiplos terminais e processo para a sua selagem da mesma
column13: "TIRA CONECTORA DE MúLTIPLOS TERMINAIS E PROCESSO PARA A SUA SELAGEM DA MESMA". A tira (1) é munida de uma série de alojamentos (2) para um número idêntico de terminais (3) aos quais fios condutores (8) acessam empurrados por uma ferramenta (11) de maneira a estabelecer conexão, por intermédio do deslocamento dos fios condutores (8) através dos terminais (3). Cada alojamento ou câmara (2) é independente daqueles adjacentes, a separação sendo constituída por intermédio de divisórias transversais (4) e (4<39>) que possibilitam o derramamento de um gel vedante no interior da respectiva câmara de alojamento (2) até um nível (12) que está em uma altura inferior àquela do degrau de entrada (10) dos fios condutores (8) e acima da borda dos terminais (3), com o objetivo de que ambos os terminais e as suas conexões com os condutores (8) sejam imersos no gel vedante de forma a prevenir a oxidação sobre as conexões.

column12: MULTI-TERMINAL CONNECTOR STRIP
column13: The strip (1) includes some (preferably special) terminals (2) housed in a manner whereby the separation (D1) between the contacts of the same wire pair (3) is equal to or less than the separation between the contacts pertaining to two different wire pairs (3), which prevents interference without the need for screening laminas. The strip (1) is completed with fastening systems (5) and (5a) for engaging on different supporting frames in which it is mounted, and also some pushbuttons (8) for operating said lugs (5). The strip finds application preferentially in the field of high-density connections employed in telecommunications, where the transmission rate of data-type signals is high.

column13: "ARQUITETURA DE CONEXãO PARA REDES XDSL E QUADRO DE DISTRIBUIçãO INTERMEDIáRIA REQUERIDO PELA DITA ARQUITETURA". A arquitetura de conexão permite de forma digital monitorar os filtros, diretamente conectando a mesa de teste com o quadro de distribuição intermediária sem requerer fiação com o DSLAM, de modo que no dito quadro de distribuição intermediária podem ser colocadas as placas de filtro do operador dominante e de segundos operadores, pelo menos uma placa inteligente contendo os relés que são ativados a partir da mesa de teste, para a qual um barramento digital é utilizado, permitindo medir o circuito do assinante para filtros de segundos operadores e o sinal do DSLAM bem como para o operador dominante, adicionalmente sendo proporcionada com uma placa adicional encarregada de receber e distribuir o sinal que chega a partir do DSLAM, entre os filtros e conectores com os quais estão conectadas placas de filtro, de modo que quando extraindo as mesmas, a entrada (voz) fica conectada com a saída (voz + dados) de modo que o sinal de voz não é desconectado.

EN DICHO MARCO SE INSTALA UNA TARJETA INTELIGENTE QUE PERMITE CONECTAR LA MESA DE PRUEBAS CON EL MARCO, CONTENIENDO DICHA TARJETA DISPOSITIVOS QUE PUEDEN SER ACTIVADOS DESDE LA MESA DE PRUEBAS PARA MONITOREAR DIGITALMENTE Y EN FORMA AUTOMATICA LOS FILTROS O DIVISORES; Y ADEMAS DICHA TARJETA PERMITE MONITOREAR EL CIRCUITO DE SUSCRIPTORES DE LAS TARJETAS DE FILTRO CUANDO SE PROVEEN FILTROS PARA LINEAS ARRENDADAS A OTROS OPERADORES; Y PERMITE COLOCAR FILTROS DE SEGUNDOS OPERADORES EN EL MISMO MARCO. LAS TARJETAS INTELIGENTES SE ACTIVAN DESDE LA MESA DE PRUEBAS POR MEDIO DE UN CANAL (BUS) DIGITAL. EN EL MARCO SE ENCUENTRAN UBICADAS TARJETAS DE FILTRO O DIVISION, AL MENOS UNA TARJETA INTELIGENTE QUE PERMITE MONITOREAR DIGITALMENTE DICHOS FILTROS, CONECTORES DE SALIDA Y UNA TARJETA ADICIONAL (BACKPLANE) A LA CUAL LLEGA LA SENAL DESDE EL DSLAM MEDIANTE UN CONECTOR

column12: Textile dyeing process of cellulosic fibers and their blends and polyester and its blends with recycled dyeing baths
column13: A textile dyeing process for dyeing cellulosic fibers and polyester and their respective blends with other fibers in recycled dyeing baths without carrying out any intermediate depuration treatment and using reactive and direct dyes for the cellulosic fibers and dispense dyes for polyester is described. The process recycles both the water already used in a previous dyeing cycle and all added products that have not been absorbed by the textile substrate, as well as the rest of the disperse dyes that had not been depleted in the previous dyeing cycles.

column12: SEMICONDUCTOR PACKAGES WITH CAVITIES AND METHODS OF MAKING THEREOF
column13: Semiconductor packages with cavities and methods of making such semiconductor packages are described. The semiconductor package includes a semiconductor die including an interface region where various components configured to interact with an environment surrounding the package can be located. Such components include a humidity sensor, a temperature sensor, a light emitting diode, a solid-state laser, a photodiode, or the like. The semiconductor package includes an opening above the interface region to facilitate proper and adequate operations of the components. The semiconductor package also includes a polymer structure surrounding the interface region, thereby forming the opening. The polymer structure has an uneven inner sidewall profile formed by multiple layers of a polymer material.

column12: UN MÉTODO PARA PRODUCIR UN MATERIAL FIBROSO PARA HONGOS CON USO EN LA AGRICULTURA, RESTAURACIÓN ECOLÓGICA Y APLICACIONES INDUSTRIALES.
column13: La presente invención hace referencia a un método que permite el almacenamiento, transporte y entrega de propágalos fúngicos en una matriz polimérica que corresponde a microfibras o nanofibras que llevan total o parcialmente encapsulados propágulos infecciosos entre láminas fibrosas o bien adheridos sobre su superficie, lográndose un material biohibrido (fibra + hongo) que nos permite incorporar unidades celulares de determinados hongos en fibras, ya que se entiende que realizaciones previas (permiten la incorporación de sustancias químicas y otros agentes biológicos) no son las adecuadas para este grupo específicos de microorganismos, con aplicaciones en diferentes estrategias de inoculación en el campo de la agricultura, horticultura, silvicultura, remediación ecológica y áreas afines.

column12: IC having electrically isolated warpage prevention structures
column13: Disclosed aspects include a semiconductor die including a substrate having a semiconductor surface including circuitry. A top metal layer is above the semiconductor surface including top metal lines that are electrically connected through a metal stack including metal interconnects that electrically connect to the circuitry. The top metal lines are configured in a primary orientation that collectively represents at least 50% of a total length of the top metal lines in a first direction. The top metal layer includes bond pads exposed from a passivation layer. The metal features are positioned lateral to and not directly electrically connected to the top metal layer and/or are positioned on the passivation layer. At least a majority of a total area of the metal features is not over metal interconnects. The metal features have a length direction oriented in a second direction that is at least essentially perpendicular relative to the primary orientation.
column15: ARIAS CHRISTLYN FAITH HOBRERO;;GUEVARA RAFAEL JOSE LIZARES

column12: PERFECCIONAMIENTOS INTRODUCIDOS EN INSTALACIONES Y CONEXIONES DE FILTROS ELECTRICOS DE BANDA ANCHA.
column13: Perfeccionamientos introducidos en instalaciones y conexiones de filtros eléctricos de banda ancha. Consiste en sustituir el clásico conjunto de conexión de la tarjeta de filtros (1'') al correspondiente cableado (7), a base de un conector de borde de tarjeta, una placa de circuito impreso, y otros dos conectores complementarios, por una única regleta de telecomunicación (8), de contactos cerrados, que por un lado permite reducir drásticamente las dimensiones del bastidor (5'') y por otro mantener continuidad entre la entrada de voz y la correspondiente salida, ante un eventual fallo en la entrada de datos. Además se ha previsto que las tarjetas de filtros (1'') sean tarjetas individuales, es decir de un solo usuario, lo que permite la implantación unitaria de las mismas, sobre una regleta múltiple, a medida que se vaya incrementando el número de usuarios.

column12: Two piece cartridge for magnetic tapes
column13: A new type of cartridge for magnetic tapes having the same dimensions as known cartridges, i.e., approximately 64 mm. in width, 100 mm. in length and 9 to 11 mm. in thickness, wherein the cartridge is divided into two independent bodies, one acting as an auxiliary element and the other as a detachable portable element which is located within the auxiliary element. Two rotating friction rollers on the portable element provide mounting supports for the corresponding magnetic tape. The portable element has a head which bears the pressure pad and this portable element has a solidly fixed cover provided with spigots for the precise guiding and fastening of the magnetic tape.

column12: Vorrichtung zum Fördern von Kraftstoff
column13: Es sind schon Vorrichtungen zum Fördern von Kraftstoff bekannt, mit einem Filtergehäuse, das zumindest zwei nebeneinander angeordnete Filteranschlüsse aufweist und in einer Aufnahme eines Deckels, der zum Verschließen einer Öffnung eines Kraftstofftanks vorgesehen ist, austauschbar angeordnet ist. Die Filteranschlüsse werden durch das Einstecken des Filtergehäuses in die Aufnahme des Deckels jeweils mit einer Kraftstoffleitung der Vorrichtung verbunden. Das Filtergehäuse wird mit Haltemitteln in der Aufnahme gehalten. Nachteilig ist, dass die hydraulische Verbindungen zwischen den Filteranschlüssen und den Kraftstoffleitungen nach dem Einbau des Filtergehäuses in die Aufnahme des Deckels nicht zugänglich sind und dadurch nicht visuell überprüft werden können. Dies führt dazu, dass Fehler bei der Montage des Filtergehäuses, insbesondere bei einem Austausch des Filtergehäuses in den Autowerkstätten, und daraus resultierende technische Probleme, wie beispielsweise Leckagen, nicht oder nicht rechtzeitig erkannt werden. Bei der erfindungsgemäßen Vorrichtung sind die hydraulischen Verbindungen zwischen den Filteranschlüssen und den Kraftstoffleitungen bei der Montage zugänglich und dadurch überprüfbar. Erfindungsgemäß ist vorgesehen, dass ein Kupplungselement (19) vorgesehen ist, an dem die Kraftstoffleitungen (10, 12) hydraulisch angeschlossen sind und das die Kraftstoffleitungen (10, 12) in nicht vertauschbarer Weise mit den Filteranschlüssen (4, 5) des Filtergehäuses (3) lösbar verbindet.

column12: Vorrichtung zum Fördern von Kraftstoff
column13: Es sind schon Vorrichtungen zum Fördern von Kraftstoff bekannt, mit einem Deckel zum Verschließen einer Öffnung eines Kraftstoffbehälters, mit einem an dem Deckel befestigten Filtergehäuse, wobei an dem Deckel zumindest zwei Haltemittel vorgesehen sind, die formschlüssig und kraftschlüssig mit dem Filtergehäuse zusammenwirken und dieses in einer Aufnahme des Deckels halten. Nachteilig ist, dass die Dichtheit der Verbindung zwischen dem Filtergehäuse und der Aufnahme des Deckels nicht sicher gewährleistet ist, da der Filter theoretisch falsch montiert oder gar ein falscher Filter eingesetzt werden könnte. Bei der erfindungsgemäßen Vorrichtung wird der Filter bei der Montage in einer definierten Position angeordnet und anschließend in dieser Position sicher gehalten. Auf diese Weise werden Leckagen vermieden. Erfindungsgemäß ist vorgesehen, dass am Filtergehäuse (4) Auskragungen (12) vorgesehen sind, die durch Drehbewegung des Filtergehäuses (4) in den Formschluss mit den Haltemitteln (9) bewegbar sind, wobei zur Sicherung des Formschlusses zusätzlich eine mechanische Verbindung (13) vorgesehen ist.

column13: resumo patente de invenção: "filtro de líquido". a presente invenção refere-se a um filtro de líquido (100), especialmente um filtro de combustível, abrangendo uma caixa de filtro (200) com uma cobertura (210), sendo que a cobertura (210) apresenta, pelo menos, uma abertura de cobertura (220), e abrangendo um cartucho de filtro (300) com uma tampa de extremidade (310) disposta na caixa de filtro (200), sendo que a tampa de extremidade (310) apresenta uma manga (320) que está projetada em forma de tubo. para possibilitar uma substituição simples e sem confusão do cartucho de filtro (300) no filtro de líquido (100), é previsto, neste caso, que a manga (320) engate através da abertura de cobertura (220) e, por meio de uma extremidade de conexão (326), se projete para fora da caixa de filtro (200). a invenção refere-se também ao uso de um filtro de líquido (100) em um sistema de alimentação de combustível de um veículo automotor, o qual abrange também um depósito de combustível disposto corrente acima do filtro de líquido (100) e um dispositivo de injeção para combustível disposto corrente abaixo do filtro de líquido (100). a invenção refere-se ainda a um cartucho de filtro (300) para ser usado em um filtro de líquido (100).

column12: Flüssigkeitsfilter
column13: Die Erfindung betrifft einen Flüssigkeitsfilter (100), insbesondere Kraftstofffilter, umfassend ein Filtergehäuse (200) mit einem Deckel (210), wobei der Deckel (210) wenigsten eine Deckelöffnung (220) aufweist und umfassend einen im Filtergehäuse (200) angeordneten Filtereinsatz (300) mit einer Endkappe (310), wobei die Endkappe (310) einen Stutzen (320) aufweist, der rohrartig ausgebildet ist. Um einen möglichst einfachen und verwechslungssicheren Austausch des Filtereinsatzes (300) im Flüssigkeitsfilter (100) zu ermöglichen, ist dabei vorgesehen, dass der Stutzen (320) die Deckelöffnung (220) durchgreift und mit einem Anschlussende (326) aus dem Filtergehäuse (200) herausragt. Die Erfindung betrifft weiterhin die Verwendung eines Flüssigkeitsfilters (100) in einem Kraftstoffversorgungssystem eines Kraftfahrzeugs, welches weiterhin einen stromaufwärts des Flüssigkeitsfilters (100) angeordneten Kraftstoffspeicher und eine stromabwärts des Flüssigkeitsfilters (100) angeordnete Einspritzvorrichtung für Kraftstoff umfasst. Die Erfindung betrifft weiterhin einen Filtereinsatz (300) zur Verwendung in einem Flüssigkeitsfilter (100).

column12: LIQUID FILTER
column13: The invention relates to a liquid filter (100), in particular a fuel filter, comprising a filter housing (200) with a cover (210), which has at least one cover opening (220), and comprising a filter insert (300), which is arranged in the filter housing (200) and comprises an end cap (310), said end cap (310) having a connecting piece (320) which has a tubular shape. The aim of the invention is to allow the filter insert (300) in the liquid filter (100) to be replaced in the simplest manner possible without causing confusion. This is achieved in that the connecting piece (320) engages through the cover opening (220), and an attachment end (326) of the connecting piece protrudes out of the filter housing (200). The invention further relates to the use of a liquid filter (100) in a fuel supply system of a motor vehicle, said system further comprising a fuel store arranged upstream of the liquid filter (100) and a fuel injection device arranged downstream of the liquid filter (100) for fuel. The invention additionally relates to a filter insert (300) for use in a liquid filter (100).

LE DOMAINE DE L'INVENTION EST CELUI DES CATALYSEURS UTILISES POUR LA CONVERSION DES HYDROCARBURES LOURDS EN HYDROCARBURES LEGERS. LE BUT DE L'INVENTION EST D'APPLIQUER UNE METHODE DE FABRICATION DU CATALYSEUR, PERMETTANT D'OBTENIR UN CATALYSEUR PLUS PERFORMANT.

LE CATALYSEUR EST PREFERENTIELLEMENT UTILISE, EN PRESENCE D'HYDROGENE, AVEC LES HYDROCARBURES LOURDS CONTENANT UN DEGRE ELEVE DE METAUX ET D'ASPHALTENES.

column12: Online intermediation system for comparison of vehicles with safe identification of users, transaction management and assistance in conflict (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: The invention proposes a system for the management of vehicle sharing agreements. Beyond facilitating the discovery of opportunities to travel in a shared vehicle, the system authenticates users to others in a secure manner through key exchanges based on asymmetric cryptography, which in turn serve to certify the start of travel in shared vehicle as agreed. With this, the system can consolidate payments automatically, avoiding the exchange of money in situ between drivers and passengers. Similar key exchanges are used to certify the correct completion of journeys. In case of possible breaches of agreements, the system uses geolocation techniques of mobile terminals to offer a set of guarantees for drivers and passengers, including compensatory payments. column12: PREPARATION OF NOVEL HETEROGENEOUS CATALYSTS OF ZINC SILICATES ACTIVATED WITH KF FOR THE SYNTHESIS OF BIODIESEL FROM VEGETABLE OILS.
column13: The invention provides porous catalysts based on silica and zinc salt and KF, which effectively promote transesterification reactions, the catalysts being easily recycled, stable even after a repeated use. The catalysts have surface areas ranging from 12 to 32 m2 per gram. These catalysts may convert vegetable oil and animal fat, in a quick manner and under soft conditions, into alkyl (C10-C30), alkyl ester and glycerin, which are mechanically separated in an easy manner. The invention refers but it is no limited to a method for the transesterification of an ester, a mono or diglyceride or vegetable oil or animal fat, for preparing an alkyl ester (C1-C4) consisting in: combining the ester, an alcohol (C1-C4) and the catalyst of the invention under conditions where said catalyst promotes the formation of the alkyl ester (c1-c4). The invention also provides a method for preparing mesoporous silicate obtained from zinc chloride and KF, which consists in the combination of silica gel and deionized water and sodium hydroxide, for forming a first mixture at not more than 40°C; and then obtain a zinc silicate by the addition of a solution of a zinc halide and KF, the resulting mixture being heated at 40-100°C, which may be isolated by filtration.

column12: PREPARATION OF NOVEL HETEROGENEOUS CATALYSTS OF ZINC SILICATES FOR THE SYNTHESIS OF BIODIESEL RESULTING FROM VEGETABLE OILS.
column13: The invention provides porous catalysts based on silica and zinc, which effectively promote transesterification reactions, the catalysts being easily recycled, stable even after a repeated use. These catalysts have surface areas ranging from 4.42 to 20.524 m2 and may convert vegetable oil and animal fat, in a quick manner and under soft conditions, into alkyl (C10-C30), alkyl ester and glycerin, which are mechanically separated in an easy manner. The invention refers but it is no limited to a method for the transesterification of an ester, a mono or diglyceride or vegetable oil or animal fat, for preparing an alkyl ester (C1-C4) consisting in: combining the ester, an alcohol (C1-C4) and the catalyst of the invention under conditions where said catalyst promotes the formation of the alkyl ester (C1-C4). The invention also provides a method for preparing mesoporous silicate obtained from zinc, which consists in the combination of silica gel and deionized water and sodium hydroxide, for forming a first mixture at not more than 40°C; and then obtain a zinc silicate by the addition of a solution of a zinc halide, the resulting mixture being heated at 70-95°C, which may be isolated by filtration.

column13: Agitator and gas diffuser system in liquids and liquids in other immiscible liquids. The object of the present invention is a novel system that can act as a diffuser and as a stirrer simultaneously. The diffusion can be of a gas in a liquid or of a liquid in another liquid, both immiscible with each other. Since the diffusion process, both of gas and liquid, is carried out, respectively, by bubbles and drops of micrometric diameter and controllable using devices whose cross section is constituted by aerodynamic profiles and being the midline that joins the different sections closed, the invention has a high efficiency in terms of diffusion and agitation processes. column12: SISTEMA DE INTERMEDIACION EN LINEA PARA COMPARTICION DE VEHICULOS CON IDENTIFICACION SEGURA DE USUARIOS, GESTION DE TRANSACCIONES Y ASISTENCIA EN CONFLICTOS
column13: La invención propone un sistema para la gestión de acuerdos de compartición de vehículo. Más allá de facilitar el descubrimiento de oportunidades para realizar desplazamientos en vehículo compartido, el sistema autentifica a unos usuarios ante otros de manera segura por medio de intercambios de claves basados en criptografía asimétrica, que sirven a su vez para certificar el inicio de los desplazamientos en vehículo compartido según lo acordado. Con ello, el sistema puede consolidar pagos automáticamente, evitando el intercambio de dinero in situ entre conductores y pasajeros. Intercambios de clave análogos sirven para certificar la finalización correcta de los desplazamientos. En caso de posibles incumplimientos de acuerdos, el sistema recurre a técnicas de geolocalización de terminales móviles para ofrecer un conjunto de garantías para conductores y pasajeros, incluyendo pagos compensatorios.

column12: Method and apparatus for detecting microorganisms
column13: The invention relates to a method and apparatus for detecting and/or identifying the presence of microorganisms in samples, including the following stages: obtaining a database which establishes a correlation between at least one parameter and a plurality of microorganisms, among which said microorganism is included; analyzing said sample in a calorimeter which supplies an electrical signal proportional to the energy given off by said sample; obtaining a curve which relates said electrical signal with respect to time; extracting from said curve at least one parameter indicative of the behavior of said microorganism; and comparing said parameter extracted from said curve with said parameter contained in said database to establish a conclusion as to the presence of said microorganism in said sample. The stage of extracting at least one parameter indicative of the behavior of said microorganism from said curve can include the division of said curve into at least two sections and the mathematical adjustment of each of said sections to two different mathematical equations, at least one of said sections adjusted to an exponential equation and/or at least another one of said sections is adjusted to a polynomial equation.

column12: Measuring apparatus, venturi and venturi insertion tool
column13: This invention comprises a system for measurement of temperature and pressure in oil wells. It comprises a single hybrid mandrel housing a double pressure and temperature optical sensor, capable of measuring temperature and pressure both in the ring and in the production tubing of an oil well and an insertable venturi tube inserted in the direction of a pressure differential optical sensor, capable of taking flow rate measurements, the installation aspects of which are substantially simplified. With the proposed construction, it is possible for one single hybrid mandrel ( 30 ) to read the pressure and temperature in the ring and tubing and the flow rate. With this, changes of flow rate are also possible, without the need to stop production for long periods for the hybrid mandrel ( 30 ) to be replaced, the mere replacement of the insertable venturi ( 12 ) sufficing, by means of an insertion and extraction GS tool ( 17 ), which is an operation requiring a much shorter time.

column12: equipamento para medição óptica de dupla temperatura e pressão e de vazão e respectiva ferramenta de manuseio
column13: A presente invenção compreende um sistema para medição de temperatura e pressão em poços de petróleo. Consta de um único mandril híbrido onde são alocados um sensor óptico de dupla pressão e temperatura, capaz de efetuar medições de temperatura e pressão tanto no anular quanto na coluna de produção de um poço de petróleo e um tubo venturi insertável inserido na direção de um sensor óptico de diferencial de pressão, capaz de efetuar medições de vazão, cujos aspectos de instalação são substancialmente facilitados. A construção proposta permite que um único mandril híbrido (30) faça as leituras de pressão e temperatura no anular e na coluna e vazão. Também permite variações de vazão sem necessidade de parar a produção por longos períodos para substituição do mandril híbrido (30), bastando apenas a substituição do venturi insertável (12) por meio de uma ferramenta GS (17) de inserção e extração, o que é uma operação que demanda um tempo muito menor.

column12: EQUIPO PARA MEDICION OPTICA DE DOBLE TEMPERATURA Y PRESION Y DE CAUDAL, Y HERRAMIENTA PARA SU MANIPULACION
column13: La presente solicitud comprende un sistema para medicion de temperatura y presion en pozos de petroleo. El mismo consta de un unico mandril híbrido, en el cual son dispuestos un sensor optico de doble presion y temperatura, capaz de efectuar mediciones de temperatura y presion, tanto en el espacio anular como también en la columna de produccion de un pozo de petroleo, y un tubo venturi insertable insertado en la direccion de un sensor optico de presion diferencial, capaz de efectuar mediciones de caudal, cuyos aspectos de instalacion se facilitan sustancialmente. La construccion propuesta permite que un unico mandril híbrido (30) realice las lecturas de presion y temperatura en el espacio anular y en la columna, y de caudal. También permite variaciones de caudal sin necesidad de detener la produccion durante períodos prolongados para sustituir el mandril híbrido (30), siendo suficiente apenas la sustitucion del venturi insertable (12) por medio de una herramienta GS (17) de insercion y extraccion, lo cual es una operacion que demanda un tiempo considerablemente menor.

column12: Triple flame section burner
column13: The present invention relates to the field of burners, particularly in burners intended for household use, such as stoves. A three ring burner is described, which produces longer and more inclined flames through which a more efficient heating is accomplished; combustion ports in the rings with straight or helicoid arrangements; where the inner ring can function in conjunction with or independently from the other two flame rings, thus controlling the heating intensity and the flame by means of controlling the velocity of the gas-air current; as main parts comprising; a burner head, which contains three concentric flame rings, one inner ring, one intermediate ring and one outer ring, each flame ring containing combustion ports, the collection of combustion ports are helicoid both in their inner ring as well as the outer ring, two lids on the burner head, one inner and the other outer; one cover for the burners which forms the surface of the heating apparatus; Venturi ducts on the lower part of the burner head; a support firmly joined to the surface of the heating apparatus, in this support are lodged Venturi ducts from the burner head; a gas distributor lodged in the lower part of the support, where the gas distributor has three gas exits, two laterals and one central.

column13: QUEIMADOR DE TRES SETORES DE CHAMA. A invenção refere-se ao campo dos queimadores, particularmente queimadores destinados a uso doméstico, tal como fogões. column12: DELTA BURNER
column13: A gas burner for household use equipment which contains a zone for the mixture of combustible gas with primary air to form an air-gas mixture, an inner chamber with an inner table, three sides with crenellated walls, each side with two ends, a vertex is formed on each end of the side and each side is formed by at least two curved surfaces which are intersected by each other, a port zone on an upper face of the crenellated wall, the port zone with main ports, the main ports are substantially centric regarding the vertexes, the symmetry axis of each one of the main ports is aligned towards the vertex closest to each one of the ports and the ports having an equidistant space between each other, a lid which closes the inner chamber of and allows the passage of the mixture through the main ports. column12: METHOD AND DEVICE FOR DETECTING MICRO-ORGANISMS
column13: The invention relates to a method and device for detecting and/or identifying the presence of micro-organisms in samples, which includes the following steps: obtaining a database that establishes a correlation between at least one parameter and a plurality of micro-organisms, among which is said micro-organism; analysing said sample in a calorimeter that supplies an electrical signal proportional to the energy released by said sample; obtaining a curve that shows said electric sample in relation to time; extracting from said curve at least one parameter that is indicative of the behaviour of said micro-organism; and comparing said parameter extracted from said curve with said parameter contained in said database in order to establish a conclusion regarding the presence of said micro-organism in said sample. The step of extracting from said curve at least one parameter that is indicative of the behaviour of said micro-organism can include dividing said curve into at least two sections and mathematically adjusting each one of said sections to two different mathematical equations, at least one of said sections being adjusted to an exponential equation and/or at least one other one of said sections being adjusted to a polynomial equation.

column12: VACUUM SWING CALCINATION PROCESS TO PRODUCE HIGH PURITY CO2 FROM CACO3
column13: This invention discloses a calcination process to produce high purity CO2 from solids containing CaCO3 which operates cyclically and continuously on the solids, arranged in a packed or a moving bed, and wherein each cycle comprises a first step where the combustion at atmospheric pressure of a fuel in the bed of solids containing CaCO3 heats them up to 800-900°C and a second step wherein a vacuum pressure between 0.05 and 0.5 atm is applied to extract pure CO2 from the solids containing CaCO3 while cooling them by 30-200°C. Said combustion can be carried out directly with air, oxygen enriched air or O2/CO2 mixtures when the process is applied to the calcination of a continuous flow of limestone in a moving bed shaft kiln. The process is also applied to calcine CaCO3 formed in reversible calcium looping processes comprising a carbonation reaction step to form CaCO3 from CaO.

column12: Trípode con adaptación inteligente a cualquier tipo de superficie que comprende sistema electrónico, mecánico y de control
column13: La presente invención hace referencia a un trípode con adaptación inteligente a cualquier tipo de superficie que comprende sistema electrónico, mecánico y de control, es útil cuando el usuario debe prestar atención en el enfoque del objetivo sin distraerse en el sistema de soporte para darle estabilidad al dispositivo óptico, lo cual es un requerimiento importante para así obtener en fotografía y filmación imágenes de calidad. El trípode con adaptación inteligente a cualquier tipo de superficie que comprende sistema electrónico, mecánico y de control, está compuesto por tres patas accionadas cada una de ellas por un tornillo sinfín de paso circular, con dientes circulares actuados por un motor con reductor y controlado automáticamente desde un sistema embebido.

column12: MOUNTING FOR INSTRUMENTS ON BUILDINGS AND METHOD FOR INSTALLING SAME
column13: The invention relates to a mounting for instruments on buildings which can be easily adapted to sloping and flat roofs and can also be permanently attached to outer walls, the aim of which is to support and securely hold various scientific and/or technological devices for the measurement of thermodynamic and meteorological parameters, among others. The mounting includes a base (3), a number of legs (2) that are connected by one end to the base (3) and are movable along same in order to adapt to the shape of the building, at least one mast (4) that is connected by one of the ends thereof to the base (3), and attachment arms (5) that are connected to the mast (4) in order to hold the instruments. In addition, the mounting includes counterweights (1) for increasing the stability thereof, located on the free ends of the legs (2) and movable along same. The present invention also relates to the method for installing said mounting.
