column12: Extraccion y aislamiento de aminoácidos en estado libre o ligado en minerales quelados
column13: La presente invención describe un proceso innovador, sensible, preciso y exacto, además de ser muy práctico para realizar la extracción, aislamiento y cuantificación de aminoácidos como Alanina, Asparagina, Aspartato, Cisteina, Glicina, Glutamato, Glutamina, Hidroxiprolina, Serina y Tirosina, entre otros, que generalmente por ser compuestos de bajo peso molecular se utilizan para la formación de quelatos con minerales, debido a que estos presentan una mejor absorción en el organismo al formar el ligando con el mineral. La extracción y aislamiento del aminoácido (libre) que no se ha unido al mineral se realiza a pH controlado mediante el uso de una solución buffer.La extracción del aminoácido ligado químicamente al mineral y su aislamiento se realiza a un pH controlado mediante el uso de un sistema buffer seguido de calentamiento y agitación de toda la mezcla, y luego se procede a filtrar.Una vez se realiza la extracción y aislamiento de las muestras, se prepara una solución estándar de concentración conocida con los aminoácidos de interés, y tanto las muestras como los estándares son derivatizados con un exceso del agente derivatizante controlando variables como pH, temperatura y agitación; luego son analizados por cromatografía líquida de alta eficiencia, usando como fase móvil una solución buffer compuesta por una sal inorgánica y un solvente orgánico, la separación se realiza en una columna C18, y se inyectan cantidades iguales de estándar y muestra, seguidamente se determina el contenido de cada aminoácido (libre o ligado) por comparación de las áreas del estándar y la muestra del aminoácido de interés en los cromatogramas obtenidos.

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO PARA LA ELABORACION DE CECINA DE CHIVO DE VEGACERVERA.
column13: Procedimiento para la elaboración de cecina de chivo de Vegacervera". Se describe un procedimiento para la elaboración de productos conocidos como "cecina de chivo de Vegacervera", que comprenden la pierna, la paletilla y los costrabazos delantero y trasero del ganado caprino. El procedimiento comprende varias fases sucesivas, entre las que se incluye una fase de salado; una fase de lavado, escurrido y adobado; una fase de colgado y ahumado, y una última fase de secado-curación. Las distintas fases se llevan a cabo en condiciones controladas de temperatura y humedad relativa, mientras que como material de adobo se utiliza una mezcla compuesta por agua, pimentón dulce, aceite de oliva y ajo.

column12: COMPOSICAO QUE E ABSORVENTE E INIBIDORA DA FORMACAO DE MAUS CHEIROS EM CAMAS DE ANIMAIS, PROCESSO PARA A SUA PREPARACAO E UTILIZACAO EM CAMAS HIGIENICAS PARA GATOS
column13: A new composition which is absorbent and inhibitive of the formation of bad smells in absorbent hygienic litter for animals that comprises a carrier and a molecular complex is described. The carrier is a porous, granular, solid, clayish, mineral substrate with a high specific surface, with a high liquid absorption capacity. The molecular complex is a mixture of natural and/or synthetic organic compounds, some identical to natural ones, with properties inhibitive of bad smells, caused by the products of bacterial degradation of cat urine, by means of specific reactions of neutralization thereof. The molecular complex is basically retained inside the structure of the particles of the carrier, in such a way that the inhibitive activity thereof is regulated and strengthened by the physicochemical properties of the carrier. Preferably, the molecular complex is present in the composition in a conclentration of 0.02 to 2% of the total weight thereof. <IMAGE>

column12: METHOD OF GENERATION OF MICROMETRIC AND SUBMICROMETRIC DROPS AND BUBBLES BY MEANS OF VISCOUS COFLOWS
column13: The present invention describes a method for generating small drops or bubbles (disperse phase) within a continuous phase, wherein both fluids are inmiscible. The size range of the drops obtained by this method can range from one millimetre to sizes less than one micron (minimum sizes of drops of the order of 100 nanometres). In addition, the size range of bubbles obtained by this method is between one millimetre and one micron. The resulting monodisperse foam is useful for materials science and for the food industry.

column13: A new composition which is absorbent and inhibitive of the formation of bad smells in absorbent hygienic litter for animals that comprises a carrier and a molecular complex is described. The carrier is a porous, granular, solid, clayish, mineral substrate with a high specific surface, with a high liquid absorption capacity. The molecular complex is a mixture of natural and/or synthetic organic compounds, some identical to natural ones, with properties inhibitive of bad smells, caused by the products of bacterial degradation of cat urine, by means of specific reactions of neutralization thereof. The molecular complex is basically retained inside the structure of the particles of the carrier, in such a way that the inhibitive activity thereof is regulated and strengthened by the physicochemical properties of the carrier. column12: Document content classification and alteration
column13: A device may receive a document including text, images, and one or more embedded documents. The device may parse the document to identify a content segment in the document. The device may determine a context for the content segment, wherein the context includes at least one of an entity identified by the content segment, a semantic meaning of the content segment, or an object identified by the content segment. The device may classify the content segment using a content classification model and based on the context for the content segment. The device may selectively alter the content segment based at least in part on a set of alteration rules, to generate a modified document. The device may provide the modified document based on selectively altering the content segment.

column12: ON-DEMAND AND SCALABLE TUNNEL MANAGEMENT IN A MULTI-CLOUD AND ON-PREMISES ENVIRONMENT
column13: Techniques are described for dynamically establishing and scaling IPSec tunnels to connect hundreds of sites of a network by making use of the user intent of connecting certain applications for applying security policies and translating it dynamically based on the location and needs of the workloads to set up the network on demand. The techniques involve a tight loop between the network controller of a site (e.g., a cloud Application Policy Infrastructure Controller) and the inter-site or multi-cloud inter-connect controller, stitched through services that enable security and network automation at scale. In particular, to control the number of IPSec tunnels, IPSec tunnels are established only when required. Additionally, IPSec tunnels may be eliminated when no longer required. Thus, resources of a network may be used in a measured way that is necessary and sufficient to meet network traffic demand.

column12: COMPARADOR DE FRECUENCIA Y FASE TOTALMENTE DIGITAL
column13: Comparador de frecuencia y fase totalmente digital está relacionado con el campo de la técnica eléctrónica y de las comunicaciones, y está destinado para proveer una salida que sea proporcional a la diferencia de fase entre dos senales de entrada siempre que esta no sobrepase los límites + pi 3,14 y - pi 3,14 , caso en el cual el circuito mantiene un valor mínimo o máximo hasta que las senales de entrada se sincronicen nuevamente en frecuencia. A diferencia de los esquemas existentes, las magnitudes angulares de entrada y el valor de la salida se expresan en forma totalmente digital, y los bloques utilizados para el procesamiento aritmético de estas magnitudes con circuitos integrados digitales, todo lo cual permite obtener una elevada precisión y una realización más compacta y confiable. La comparación de frecuencia se logra mediante el empleo de una máquina secuencial sincrónica, la cual posee tres estados que se asocian respectivamente a la operación normal y a los dos sentidos posibles de la diferencia de frecuencia entre las senales que se comparan.

column12: SYSTEM FOR COUPLING A TOOTH TO ITS TOOTH HOLDER IN AN EXCAVATOR OR THE LIKE
column13: The invention relates to a system for coupling a tooth to its tooth holder in an excavator or the like, wherein the tooth holder is provided with guiding means so that the ears of the tooth in horizontal position can slide vertically guided by the shafts of said ears to a point in which the cavity of the tooth is aligned with the axis of the nose of the tooth holder. The tooth is then displaced in the direction of said axes and in a direction in which the tooth approaches the tooth holder until the shafts of the ears of the tooth are placed in complementary slots of the tooth holder, which are located at the same level as the shafts thereby creating a gap between the tooth holder guiding means and the shafts of the tooth, a pin being inserted in said gap.

column13: A new composition which is absorbent and inhibitive of the formation of bad smells in absorbent hygienic litter for animals that comprises a carrier and a molecular complex is described. The carrier is a porous, granular, solid, clayish, mineral substrate with a high specific surface, with a high liquid absorption capacity. The molecular complex is a mixture of natural and/or synthetic organic compounds, some identical to natural ones, with properties inhibitive of bad smells, caused by the products of bacterial degradation of cat urine, by means of specific reactions of neutralization thereof. The molecular complex is basically retained inside the structure of the particles of the carrier, in such a way that the inhibitive activity thereof is regulated and strengthened by the physicochemical properties of the carrier. Preferably, the molecular complex is present in the composition in a conclentration of 0.02 to 2% of the total weight thereof. <IMAGE>

column12: SYSTEM FOR COUPLING A TOOTH TO ITS TOOTH HOLDER IN AN EXCAVATOR OR THE LIKE
column13: The invention relates to a system for coupling a tooth to its tooth holder in an excavator or the like, wherein the tooth holder is provided with guiding means so that the ears of the tooth in horizontal position can slide vertically guided by the shafts of said ears to a point in which the cavity of the tooth is aligned with the axis of the nose of the tooth holder. QUE DEBIDO A SU CONTACTO CON MASAS DE MINERAL SE ENCUENTREN CONTAMINADAS CON ACIDO SULFURICO Y METALES PRECIOSOS, ASI COMO INSTALACIONES INDUSTRIALES QUE PRODUZCAN EFLUENTES ACIDOS (EJ.: INDUSTRIA GALVANOTECNICA).

column12: PROCESS FOR THE TREATMENT AND DECONTAMINATION OF ACID WATERS WHICH CONTAIN DISSOLVED METALS AND THEIR CONVERSION INTO FERTILIZERS (PIDRA PROCESS)
column13: Process for the treatment and decontamination of acid waters which contain dissolved metals and their conversion into fertilizers, comprising the combination of three specific processes: a) selective removal of iron and of the acidity of the medium through biooxidation of Fe (II) and precipitation with alkalis (Ca(OH2), NaOH, KOH or NH4OH) of Fe (III) compounds b) taking advantage of the high sulphate content of the acid waters for the synthesis, through ionic exchange, of K2SO4 or NH4SO4, free of chlorides which may be used as fertilizers or commercialised in other applications c) recovery of the metals contained in such waters: Cu<2+>, Al<3+>, Zn<2+> and Mg<2+>. The process may be applied to acid waters originating from various sources: active or inactive mine installations, river basins, water courses, lagoons, etc. which, due to their contact with numeral masses, are contaminated with sulphuric acid and heavy metals, as well as industrial plants which produce acid effluents (for example galvanotechnical industry).

column12: Polypropylene composites with reinforcement based on eggshells: procedure to obtain the said composite, reinforcement based on eggshells, and procedure for obtaining it
column13: This invention reveals polypropylene composites to be used in the automotive, electronics, packaging and textile industries, which comprises a polypropylene homopolymer in a proportion ranging from 10 to 60% by weight, a natural reinforcement based on eggshells, and an antioxidant. This invention also reveals a natural reinforcement produced from eggshells obtained as an agroindustrial waste, the process to obtain said composite, and the process to obtain such reinforcement. By means of this invention, polypropylene composites using the natural reinforcement are obtained that have improved mechanical and thermal behavior when compared to polypropylene composites using traditional mineral reinforcements.

column12: equipamento para medição óptica de dupla temperatura e pressão e de vazão
column13: a presente invenção compreende um sistema para medição de temperatura e pressão em poços de petróleo. consta de um único mandril híbrido onde são alocados um sensor óptico de dupla pressão e temperatura, capaz de efetuar medições de temperatura e pressão tanto no anular quanto na coluna de produção de um poço de petróleo e um tubo venturi insertável inserido na direção de um sensor óptico de diferencial de pressão, capaz de efetuar medições de vazão, cujos aspectos de instalação são substancialmente facilitados. a construção proposta permite que um único mandril híbrido (30) faça as leituras de pressão e temperatura no anular e na coluna e vazão. também permite variações de vazão sem necessidade de parar a produção por longos períodos para substituição do mandril híbrido (30), bastando apenas a substituição do venturi insertável (12) por meio de uma ferramenta gs (17) de inserção e extração, o que é uma operação que demanda um tempo muito menor.

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO PARA EL TRATAMIENTO Y DESCONTAMINACION DE AGUAS ACIDAS QUE CONTIENEN METALES DISUELTOS Y SU CONVERSION EN FERTILIZANTES.
column13: Procedimiento para el tratamiento y descontaminación de aguas ácidas que contienen metales disueltos y su conversión en fertilizantes que consiste en la combinación de tres procesos específicos: a) Eliminación selectiva del hierro y de la acidez del medio mediante la biooxidación de Fe (II) y precipitación con álcalis (Ca(OH){sub,2 , NaOH, KOH ó NH{sub,4 OH) de los compuestos de Fe(III). b) Aprovechamiento del elevado contenido en sulfatos de las aguas ácidas para la síntesis, mediante intercambio iónico, de K{sub,2 SO{sub,4 ó NH{sub,4 SO{sub,4 , libre de cloruros que pueden ser utilizados como fertilizantes o comercializados en otras aplicaciones. c) Recuperación de los metales contenidos en estas aguas: CU{sup,2+ , Al{sup,3+ , Zn{sup,2+ y Mg{sup,2+ . Este proceso se puede aplicar a aguas ácidas de diversas procedencias: instalaciones mineras activas o inactivas, cuencas fluviales, arroyos, lagunas, etc. que debido a su contacto con masas de mineral se encuentren contaminadas con ácido sulfúrico y metales pesados, así como instalaciones industriales que produzcan efluentes ácidos (ejemplo: industria galvanotécnica).

column12: REINFORCING FIBER AND ITS APPLICATION FOR REINFORCING CONCRETE
column13: FIELD: manufacturing technology.SUBSTANCE: invention relates to an adhesive composition for reinforcing strands of glass fibre. A strand of reinforcing fibre glass contains multiple separate glass fibres coated with adhesive composition. Adhesive composition contains at least one silane binding agent, polyurethane film-forming agent containing blocked isocyanate, secondary film-forming agent and water. Polyurethane film-forming agent containing blocked isocyanate is present in the said adhesive composition in an amount from approximately 25 WT% to approximately 75 WT% (content of solid substances) of the entire solid composition. Secondary film-forming agent is specified in epoxide, polyester, polyvinyl acetate, non-reactive polyurethane and mixtures thereof, and the said secondary film-forming agent is present in the said adhesive composition in amount of 5 WT% to 60 WT% (content of solid substances) of the entire solid composition.EFFECT: technical result consists in improvement of resistance to abrasion of the fibre.16 cl, 3 dwg, 3 tbl

column12: Equipment for optical measurement of double temperature and pressure and of flow rate and respective handling tool
column13: This invention comprises a system for measurement of temperature and pressure in oil wells. It comprises a single hybrid mandrel housing a pressure and temperature double optical sensor, capable of measuring temperature and pressure both in the ring and in the production tubing of an oil well and an insertable venturi tube inserted in the direction of a pressure differential optical sensor, capable of taking flow rate measurements, the installation aspects of which are substantially simplified. With the proposed construction, it is possible for one single hybrid mandrel (30) to read the pressure and temperature in the ring and tubing and the flow rate. With this, changes of flow rate are also possible, without the need to stop production for long periods for the hybrid mandrel (30) to be replaced, the mere replacement of the insertable venturi (12) sufficing, by means of an insertion and extraction tool (17), which is an operation requiring a much shorter time.

column12: Method and device to regulate the output bit rate in variable bit rate video coders.
column13: Applicable in compressed video transmission where the bandwidth availability of the transmission system varies with time; and which has the object of continuously matching the video compressor output rate to the occupancy conditions of the transmission system. The method has a first phase in which the level of filling of the output memory (7) of the video compressor (6) is analized, obtaining the number of reading and writing commands made on said output memory and calculating its variation in filling. In a second phase, the information concerning the output memory filling is processed, determining from the latter data and another data, the new statistical parameters that condition the operation of the video compressor, and which are sent to the latter in a third phase. The device carries out the different phases of the method.

column12: METHOD OF OBTAINING HYDROGEN FROM NATURAL GAS
column13: The invention relates to a method of obtaining hydrogen from natural gas. The inventive method comprises the following steps consisting in: (a) reacting the natural gas with a mixture of air and water vapour in a single reactor in order to obtain a gas comprising H2 and CO, (b) reacting the CO produced at high temperature with water vapour in order to obtain a gas comprising H2 and CO2, and (c) reacting the CO that has not reacted in step (b) at low temperature with water vapour in order to obtain a gas comprising H2 and CO2. The invention is characterised in that, in step (a), the natural gas, air and water vapour are supplied simultaneously and reacted on the same catalyst and in that the pressure used in steps (a) through (c) varies between 1 and 8 atm. The invention also relates to H2 production facilities that are used to perform the aforementioned method.

column12: SCALABLE, EASY-TO-DEPLOY SYSTEM AND REAGENTS THEREOF FOR CRISPR-ASSOCIATED NUCLEASE-BASED DETECTION OF PATHOGEN GENETIC MATERIAL
column13: Scalable testing of a disease or pathogenic infection is limited by hurdles in cost of reagents, instrument accessibility, availability of highly trained personnel, and large upfront investment. Herein, systems and methods for use of CRISPR-associated nuclease-based, Rugged, Equitable, Scalable Testing (CREST) are provided. CREST pairs reliable polymerase chain reaction (PCR) with low-cost instrumentation without sacrificing detection sensitivity, and allows for a binary interpretation of detection results. A new lysis solution for extraction of nucleic acids and/or protein is also provided and can be used to prepare nucleic acid sample in CREST assay. The systems and reagents disclosed provide for a point-of-care solution to increase distribution of COVID-19 surveillance.

column12: METHOD OF OBTAINING HYDROGEN FROM NATURAL GAS
column13: The invention relates to a process for obtaining hydrogen from natural gas which comprises (a) reacting the natural gas with a mixture of air and steam in a single reactor to obtain a gas comprising H 2  and CO, (b) reacting the CO produced at a high temperature with steam to obtain a gas comprising H 2  and CO 2 , and (c) reacting the CO which has not reacted in step (b) at a low temperature with steam to obtain a gas comprising H 2  and CO 2 ,  characterized in that  in step (a) the natural gas, the air and the steam are fed simultaneously and react on the same catalyst and in that the pressure used in steps (a) to (c) varies between 1 and 8 atm, as well as to a H 2  production plant for carrying out the mentioned process.

column12: Verfahren und Einrichtung zur Regulierung der Ausgangsbitrate in Videokodern mit variabler Bitrate
column13: Applicable in compressed video transmission where the bandwidth availability of the transmission system varies with time; and which has the object of continuously matching the video compressor output rate to the occupancy conditions of the transmission system. The method has a first phase in which the level of filling of the output memory (7) of the video compressor (6) is analized, obtaining the number of reading and writing commands made on said output memory and calculating its variation in filling. In a second phase, the information concerning the output memory filling is processed, determining from the latter data and another data, the new statistical parameters that condition the operation of the video compressor, and which are sent to the latter in a third phase. The device carries out the different phases of the method. <IMAGE>

column13: "sistema de leitura e aquisição de dados para sensores a fibra óptica". é descrito um sistema de leitura e aquisição de dados para sensores a fibra óptica contendo redes de bragg para o sensoriamento de parâmetros físicos oriundos de um conjunto de poços de petróleo, dito sistema compreendendo um sistema óptico (30) de processamento de sinais, ditos sinais sendo: i) provenientes de sensores (10a,10b) de parâmetros físicos instalados em um conjunto de poços e ii) resultantes do comprimento de onda refletido em resposta a uma perturbação do parâmetro físico medido; b) um sistema eletrônico (40) de processamento de sinais para converter os sinais de intensidade óptica provenientes do dito sistema óptico (30) através de detectores (36a, 36b, 36c, 36d) que otimizam a relação sinal/ruído para sinais elétricos que são digitalizados e convertidos segundo um algoritmo que utiliza as constantes das curvas de calibração de cada sensor para a determinação das grandezas físicas de pressão e temperatura; e c) um chaveador óptico (20) com uma interface entre a) e b), para ampliar o número de poços monitorados.

column13: Applicable in compressed video transmission where the bandwidth availability of the transmission system varies with time; and which has the object of continuously matching the video compressor output rate to the occupancy conditions of the transmission system. The method has a first phase in which the level of filling of the output memory (7) of the video compressor (6) is analized, obtaining the number of reading and writing commands made on said output memory and calculating its variation in filling. In a second phase, the information concerning the output memory filling is processed, determining from the latter data and another data, the new statistical parameters that condition the operation of the video compressor, and which are sent to the latter in a third phase. The device carries out the different phases of the method. <IMAGE>

column12: SISTEMA PARA LA MEDIDA Y ADQUISICION DE DATOS PARA SENSORES DE FIBRA OPTICA
column13: Sistema de lectura y adquisición de datos para sensores a fibra óptica, que contiene redes de Bragg para detectar magnitudes ffsicas provenientes de un pozo o un conjunto de pozos de petróleo, CARACTERIZÁNDOSE dicho sistema porque comprende:a. un sistema óptico de procesamiento de señales, siendo dichas señales: i) provenientes de sensores de parámetros ffsicos instalados en un pozo o conjunto de pozos y ii) resultantes de la compresión de onda reflejada en respuesta a una perturbación de la magnitud física medida;b. un sistema electrónico de procesamiento de señales para convertir las señales de intensidad óptica provenientes de dicho sistema óptico a señales eléctricas a través de detectores que optimizan la relación señal/ruido;c. un conmutador óptico con una interfase entre a) y b), para ampliar el número de pozos monitoreados. Sistema de acuerdo con la reivindicación 1, CARACTERIZADO porque las magnitudes ffsicas son presión y temperatura. Sistema de acuerdo con la reivindicación 1, CARACTERIZADO porque las redes de sensor y atenuador ffsico deben presentar espectros idénticos.<EMI FILE="05079338_1" ID="1" IMF=JPEG HE=50 WI=50 >
column15: ARIAS VIDAL JOSE LUIZ;;DA SILVA MANOEL FELICIA JR;;MUNOZ FREITAS RICARDO;;THOME FERREIRA LINCOL HOMERO

column12: SITEMA DE LECTURA Y ADQUISICION DE DATOS PARA SENSORES A FIBRA OPTICA
column13: Se describe un sistema de lectura y adquisicion de datos para sensores a fibra optica, que contiene redes de Bragg para detectar parámetros físicos provenientes de un conjunto de pozos de petroleo, comprendiendo dicho sistema un sistema optico (30) de procesamiento de senales, siendo dichas senales; i) provenientes de sensores (10a, 10b) de parámetros físicos instalados en un conjunto de pozos y ii) resultantes de la compresion de ondas reflejadas en respuesta a una perturbacion del parámetro físico medido; b) un sistema electronica (40) de procesamiento de senales para convertir las senales de intensidad optica provenientes de dicho sistema optico (30) a través de detectores (36a, 36b, 36b, 36d) que optimizan la relacion de senal/ruido a senales eléctricas que son digitalizadas y convertidas segun un algoritmo que utiliza las constantes de curvas de calibracion de cada sensor para la determinacion de las magnitudes físicas de presion y temperatura; y c) un conmutador optico (20) con una interfase entre a) y b), para ampliar el numero de pozos monitoreados.
column15: VIDAL JOSE LUIZ ARIAS;;SILVA MANOEL FELICIANO DA JUNI;;FREITAS RICARDO MUNOZ;;FERREIRA LINCOLN HOMERO THOME

column12: HEARTRATE DETECTION AND ANALYSIS SYSTEM THROUGH INFRARED LIGHT.
column13: The present disclosure is related to a system that detects and measures the heartrate by the incidence of an infrared beam in an area that is sensitive to the heartrate. The reflected signal is collected by an optical system of an infrared spectrometer which analyzes the light signal by its decomposition through its spectrum. This analog signal (light beam) is converted into a digital signal for analysis, storage and processing by means of an application. The signal is analyzed by an electronic system. There is no physical contact with the subject's skin, so this system is recommended for accident situations, natural disasters, for veterinarians and other scenarios in which it is not possible to keep the subject immobile or to have contact with his skin.

column12: METHOD OF OBTAINING HYDROGEN FROM NATURAL GAS
column13: Procedure for obtaining hydrogen from natural gas. Procedure for obtaining hydrogen from natural gas which comprises: (a) reacting natural gas with a mixture of air and water vapour, in a single reactor in order to obtain a gas which comprises H2 and CO2 (b) react the CO produced at high temperature with water vapour to obtain a gas which comprises H2 and CO2, and (c) react the CO which has not reacted in stage (b) at low temperature to water vapour to obtain a gas which comprises H2 and CO2, characterised because in stage (a) the natural gas, the air and the water vapour are fed simultaneously and react over the same catalyst and because the pressure used in stages (a) and (c) varies between 1 and 8 atm, as well as a H2 production plant to perform the procedure.

column12: Process for obtaining hydrogen from natural gas
column13: The invention relates to a process for obtaining hydrogen from natural gas which comprises (a) reacting the natural gas with a mixture of air and steam in a single reactor to obtain a gas comprising H 2 and CO, (b) reacting the CO produced at a high temperature with steam to obtain a gas comprising H 2 and CO 2 , and (c) reacting the CO which has not reacted in step (b) at a low temperature with steam to obtain a gas comprising H 2 and CO 2 , characterized in that in step (a) the natural gas, the air and the steam are fed simultaneously and react on the same catalyst and in that the pressure used in steps (a) to (c) varies between 1 and 8 atm, as well as to a H 2 production plant for carrying out the mentioned process.

column12: sistema de leitura e aquisição de dados para sensores a fibra óptica
column13: "SISTEMA DE LEITURA E AQUISIçãO DE DADOS PARA SENSORES A FIBRA óPTICA". é descrito um sistema de leitura e aquisição de dados para sensores a fibra óptica contendo redes de Bragg para o sensoriamento de parâmetros físicos oriundos de um conjunto de poços de petróleo, dito sistema compreendendo um sistema óptico (30) de processamento de sinais, ditos sinais sendo: i) provenientes de sensores (10a,10b) de parâmetros físicos instalados em um conjunto de poços e ii) resultantes do comprimento de onda refletido em resposta a uma perturbação do parâmetro físico medido; b) um sistema eletrónico (40) de processamento de sinais para converter os sinais de intensidade óptica provenientes do dito sistema óptico (30) através de detectores (36a, 36b, 36c, 36d) que otimizam a relação sinal/ruído para sinais elétricos que são digitalizados e convertidos segundo um algoritmo que utiliza as constantes das curvas de calibração de cada sensor para a determinação das grandezas físicas de pressão e temperatura; e c) um chaveador óptico (20) com uma interface entre a) e b), para ampliar o número de poços monitorados.

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO PARA LA OBTENCION DE HIDROGENO A PARTIR DE GAS NATURAL
column13: Procedimiento para la obtención de hidrógeno a partir de gas natural que comprende (a) hacer reaccionar el gas natural con una mezcla de aire y vapor de agua, en un único reactor para obtener un gas que comprende H2 y CO, (b) hacer reaccionar el CO producido a alta temperatura con vapor de agua para obtener un gas que comprende H2 y CO2, y (c) hacer reaccionar el CO que no ha reaccionado en la etapa (b) a baja temperatura con vapor de agua para obtener un gas que comprende H2 y CO2, caracterizado porque en la etapa (a) el gas natural, el aire y el vapor de agua se alimentan simultáneamente y reaccionan sobre el mismo catalizador y porque la presión empleada en las etapas (a) a (c) varía entre 1 y 8 atm, así como a una planta de producción de H2 para llevar el citado procedimiento.

column12: Improvements in atomic layer deposition on high aspect ratio electrode structures
column13: Battery electrodes using VACNT forests to create 3D electrode nanostructures and methods of making the same are described. The VACNTs are electrically and mechanically connected to an anode or cathode substrate, providing a large area of three-dimensional surface for the coating with the active material, and providing a highly conductive electron channel for the battery current collector. A variety of different active materials suitable for anodes and cathodes of lithium ion batteries can be used to coat individual carbon nanotubes. The high surface area provided by the VACNT forest and the nano-size of the coated active material enable high energy density and high power density to be achieved with the same battery. Complete conformal coating of individual CNTs may be achieved by a variety of different methods, and coating with a variety of active materials may be used to produce nanolaminate coatings having better electrochemical properties than a single material.

column12: NANOSTRUCTURED CATALYSTS HAVING A CONTROLLED SURFACE WITHOUT A NOBLE METAL, WITH A LOW LANTHANIDE CONTENT AND AN INCREASED OXYGEN-STORAGE CAPACITY AT A LOW TEMPERATURE
column13: The invention relates to catalysts having a structure comprising nanostructured oxides arranged in layers, the surface of which is formed by a cerium-zirconium mixed oxide with a pyrochlore-type structure (phase k) that can activate the hydrogen molecule at a low temperature, and the nucleus is formed by a zirconium oxide or a zirconium oxide stabilised by a dopant. The invention is part of catalytic processes wherein it is important that the catalyst has a good oxygen storage capacity, such as for example, the purification of the exhaust gases in combustion engines. The catalysts can also be applied to any other application involving reactions requiring the activation of hydrogen molecules.

column12: NANOSTRUCTURED OXIDES HAVING CONTROLLED SURFACES AND HAVING HIGH OXYGEN STORAGE CAPACITY AT LOW TEMPERATURES
column13: The present invention relates to nanostructured cerium and zirconium oxides having controlled surfaces and having the distinct characteristic of, despite having low lanthanide content, showing very good oxygen storage properties at low temperatures. In addition, said oxides are characterized in that the structure thereof is arranged in layers, the surfaces thereof are constituted by a cerium oxide and the nucleuses are constituted by a zirconium oxide or a zirconium oxide stabilized with a dopant. Said characteristics allow said oxides to be used in the formulation of three-way catalysts used in automotive vehicles and in the formulation of catalysts used in reactions for producing hydrogen for use in fuel batteries.

column12: VIRTUAL REALITY SYSTEM FOR THE EVALUATION AND TREATMENT OF MOTOR DISTURBANCES ASSOCIATED WITH NEURODEGENERATIVE DISEASES AND AGE
column13: The invention relates to a virtual reality system for the evaluation and treatment of motor disturbances associated with neurodegenerative diseases and age, comprising: a patient module, in turn including glasses (1) which capture the movement of the patient's head and which are provided with a screen device for viewing a virtual environment, reflective markers (2), infrared cameras (3) that capture the position of the reflective markers (2), a communication module (4) which receives the information captured by the glasses (1) and the infrared cameras (3) and which sends said information to processing means (5) that generate the virtual environment and an expert module including management means (6) for controlling a plurality of variables which modify and evaluate the virtual environment of the patient.

column12: APPARATUS AND METHOD FOR MASS PRODUCING A MONODISPERSE MICROBUBBLE AGENT
column13: An apparatus (1) for mass producing monodisperse microbubbles, comprising a microfluidic flow focusing device (2) including a dispersed phase fluid supply channel (110) having an outlet (114) that discharges into a flow focusing junction (140); a continuous phase fluid supply channel (120, 120') having an outlet (124) that discharges into the flow focusing junction; and a bubble formation channel (130) having an inlet (132) disposed at the flow focusing junction. The configuration of the flow focusing junction (140) is such that, in operation, a flow of dispersed phase fluid (12) discharging from the outlet (114) of the dispersed phase fluid supply channel (110) is engageable in co-flow by a focusing flow of continuous phase fluid discharging from the outlet of the at least one continuous phase fluid supply channel under formation of a gradually thinning jet of dispersed phase fluid that extends into the inlet of the bubble formation channel.

column12: MOUNTING FOR INSTRUMENTS ON BUILDINGS AND METHOD FOR INSTALLING SAME
column13: The invention relates to a mounting for instruments on buildings which can be easily adapted to sloping and flat roofs and can also be permanently attached to outer walls, the aim of which is to support and securely hold various scientific and/or technological devices for the measurement of thermodynamic and meteorological parameters, among others. The mounting includes a base (3), a number of legs (2) that are connected by one end to the base (3) and are movable along same in order to adapt to the shape of the building, at least one mast (4) that is connected by one of the ends thereof to the base (3), and attachment arms (5) that are connected to the mast (4) in order to hold the instruments. In addition, the mounting includes counterweights (1) for increasing the stability thereof, located on the free ends of the legs (2) and movable along same. The present invention also relates to the method for installing said mounting.

column12: PROCESO DE PURIFICACION Y CONCENTRACION PARA LA OBTENCION DE UNA VACUNA CONTRA LA FIEBRE AFTOSA EN 2ML.
column13: 1. PROCESO DE PURIFICACION Y CONCENTRACION PARA LA OBTENCION DE UNA VACUNA PARA LA FIEBRE AFTOSA EN 2 ml, CARACTERIZADO PORQUE SE INACTIVAN LAS SUSPEN- SIONES VIRALES DE VIRUS DE LA FIEBRE AFTOSA PRE- VIAMENTE CLOROFORMADAS, CON UNA SOLUCION DE BROMO ETILEN IMINA 3 mM A 26 GRADOS CENTIGRADOS POR 24 HORAS; POSTERIORMENTE SE ENFRIA A 4 CENTIGRADOS Y SE AGREGA LENTAMENTE Y CON AGITACION CONTINUA UNA SOLUCION DE TIMEROSAL A UNA CONCENTRACION DE 0.06 gr/litro DE ANTIGENO. PARA LUEGO REALIZAR LA CLA- RIFICACION MANTENIENDO LA TEMPERATURA DEL ANTIGENO A 4 GRADOS CENTIGRADOS CON AGITACION DE 80 A 100 R.P.M. MANTENIENDO EL ph ENTRE 8 Y 9; POSTERIOR- MENTE SE REALIZA LA ETAPA FINAL DE FILTRACION Y CONCENTRACION DEL ANTIGENO. 2. PROCESO DE PURIFICACION Y CONCENTRACION PARA LA OBTENCION DE UNA VACUNA PARA LA FIEBRE AFTOSA EN 2 ml DE ACUERDO CON LA REIVINDICACION NUMERO 1, CA- RACTERIZADO PORQUE EN LA ETAPA DE CLARIFICACION EL ph SE DEBE MANTENER ENTRE 8 Y 9 PARA LO CUAL SE AJUSTA ADICIONANDO SOLUCION DE HIDROXIDO DE POTA- SIO 0.05M A 1.5M Y CON AGITACION CONTINUA; AGRE- GANDO LUEGO SOLUCION DE FOSFATO DE SODIO (Na2 HPO4 2H20) PARA LA CONCENTRACION FINAL DE 5mM EN EL AN- TIGENO VERIFICANDO SIEMPRE EL ph; AGREGAR LUEGO LENTAMENTE Y CON AGITACION CONTINUA FRACCIONES DE UNA SOLUCION DE CLORURO DE CALCIO 6 A 8 m.M. CON- TROLANDO EL ph Y AJUSTANDOLO SI ES NECESARIO CON SOLUCION DE HIDROXIDO DE POTASIO HASTA OBTENER UN ph DE 8.5 EL ANTIGENO TRATADO 0.5 A 1M SE DEJA EN AGITACION A 4 GRADOS CENTIGRADOS POR 24 HORAS Y UN TIEMPO IGUAL A 26 GRADOS CENTIGRADOS; AL FINAL DE ESTOS TIEMPOS DE AGITACION CON CAMBIOS DE TEMPERA- TURA SE BAJA NUEVAMENTE A 4 GRADOS CENTIGRADOS SE SUSPENDE LA AGITACION Y SE DEJA SEDIMENTAR DE 6 A 8 DIAS CAMBIANDO LUEGO DE BIOREACTOR DEJANDO DE 3 A 4 DIAS SIN AGITACION HASTA EL MOMENTO DE LA FIL- TRACION. **** PENDIENTE REIVINDICACION NUMERO 3 ******

column12: Autonomous system of irrigation for survival of plants (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: The system is designed with the capacity to concentrate and store the rainwater and to lead it towards a hydraulic distribution network (2) equipped with capsules (9) for irrigation by exudation, allowing during the periods of drought the minimum quantity of water necessary for avoid the death of the plants, favoring the successful implantation of said plants in the execution of revegetation, reforestation, landscaping and similar projects. The system initially comprises a rainwater storage vessel (1), through a cover (3) on the bottom of which an orifice (4) has been established that drains the rain towards the storage container (1), counting the latter. With an outlet (6) to the hydraulic network (2). The system is designed to operate autonomously and without any auxiliary energy, being the suction voltage exerted by the soil to dry which causes the circulation of water, activating irrigation only when it is necessary to ensure the survival of the plant . column12: PROCEDIMIENTO PARA LA OBTENCIÓN SEMICONTINUA DE ALCOHOL
column13: La invención se relaciona con la biotecnología, el objetivo técnico que persigue la misma, es desarrollar un procedimiento para producir alcohol utilizando levaduras inmovilizadas en soportes. La esencia de la invención consiste en el empleo como soporte de astillas de madera de balsa, lavadas previamente con agua caliente de 40-100oC y colocadas en un reactor en una proporción con el medio de 5-40% y aireado el mismo de 0.5-1.0 litro de medio por minuto, logrando así la adsorción de las células al empaque, posteriormente se disminuye la aireación y se pasa a la etapa de producción de alcohol que dura de 4-8 horas. La invención puede ser aplicada en la producción de vinagre, antibióticos o cualquier proceso de biosíntesis de productos orgánicos por vía microbiana donde el producto final no sea biomasa.

The biopolymer comprises at least a bioactive domain capable of directing in a precise manner the formation of a solid or semisolid implant. column13: The present invention relates to a biopolymer, bioactive and totally biocompatible, very fluid at ambient temperature, capable of gelling in a sudden manner at 37 C, forming a solid implant, structurally integral and continuous having high mechanical properties. The biopolymer comprises at least a bioactive domain capable of directing in a precise manner the formation of a solid or semisolid implant. Furthermore the invention relates to any of the nucleic acids encoding the amino acid sequence of the biopolymer, implants, pharmaceutically acceptable vehicles, uses thereof, and a method of synthesis thereof.

column12: Biopolímero, implante que lo comprende y sus usos
column13: La presente invención se refiere a un biopolímero, bioactivo y totalmente biocompatible, muy fluido a temperatura ambiente y con capacidad de gelificar de forma brusca a 37 ºC; formando un implante sólido estructuralmente integro, continuo y con altas prestaciones mecánicas. El biopolímero comprende al menos un dominio bioactivo capaz de dirigir de forma precisa la formación de un implante sólido o semi-sólido. Asimismo la invención se refiere a cualquiera de los ácidos nucleicos que codifican para la secuencia aminoacídica del biopolímero, implantes, vehículos farmacéuticamenteaceptables, a sus usos y a un método de síntesis del mismo.

column12: USO DE AMINOACIDOS CICLICOS NO PROLINICOS PARA AUMENTAR LA TOLERANCIA DE PLANTAS A CONDICIONES DE ESTRES OSMOTICO
column13: Se refiere a un compuesto de formula (I) donde: n es 0, 1; Y es -C=O, -CH2; X es -OH, -O-C1-4 alquilo, -NH-C1-4alquilo; y Z es H, -OH, -O-C1-4alquilo, -NH-C1-4alquilo; y Z puede ser H, -OH, -SH o -S-C1-4alquilo, con la condicion de que L-prolina y D-prolina estan excluidas. Dicho compuesto es util para aumentar la tolerancia de plantas a condiciones de estres osmotico, tales como el estres salino o el deficit hidrico.

column12: CONVERSOR DIGITAL/ANALOGICO QUE GENERA FORMAS DE ONDA DE TIPO EXPONENCIAL DECRECIENTE PARA EL LAZO DE REALIMENTACION DE UN CONVERSOR SIGMA-DELTA DE TIEMPO CONTINUO.
column13: El circuito conversor Digital/Analógico propuesto genera formas de onda de tipo exponencial decreciente para el lazo de realimentaci6n de un conversor Sigma-Delta de tiempo continuo. Permite reducir notablemente la sensibilidad al jitter del reloj de los conversores Sigma-Delta de tiempo continuo. Consiste en un condensador (3), dos resistencias (6) y seis conmutadores (2), (4) y (5) los cuales están controlados por el correspondiente circuito de lógica (Figura 5). En realidad, se han utilizado dos condensadores (3) con sus terminales cruzados para considerar las capacidades parásitas asociadas a la placa inferior del condensador con el sustrato. El circuito que se propone logra una notable reducción de esa sensibilidad al jitter mediante la generación de formas de onda de tipo retorno a cero con retraso de medio ciclo (HRZ) y con evolución exponencial decreciente en el lazo de realimentación del conversor Sigma-Delta en tiempo continuo.

column12: FIBER OPTIC POSITION TRANSDUCER WITH MAGNETOSTRICTIVE MATERIAL AND POSITION CALIBRATION PROCESS.
column13: Fiber optic position transducer that includes a magnetic or electromagnetic element, one or more segments of magnetostrictive material, Fiber Bragg Grating Sensors, a rod of material that is impenetrable to magnetic fields, optical fiber. One or more of the sensors is fixed upon a segment of magnetostrictive material, which is fixed to a rod, and may only be displaced longitudinally. The Fiber Bragg Grating Sensors have different wavelengths and are made of the same optical fiber. The magnetic or electromagnetic element included may be made of NdFeB (Neodymium Iron Boron) or metal alloys of TbDyFe (Terbium, Dysprosium and Iron), such as TX, Terphenol-D and others. It is applied to a control flow valve in an oil well, and it also refers to the calibration process of the position of the transducer.

column13: PROTEINA NIGRINA B DE LA PLANTA SAMBUCUS NIGRA L., PROCEDIMIENTO PARA SU OBTENCION Y SU UTILIZACION. LA NIGRINA B ES UNA PROTEINA VEGETAL INACTIVADORA DE RIBOSOMAS DEL TIPO DE DOS CADENA A Y B CON UNA MASA MOLECULAR RELATIVA A 26.600 Y 31.600 RESPECTIVAMENTE. EL PROCEDIMIENTO COMPRENDE: EXTRAER LA PLANTA SAMBUCUS NIGRA L., FILTRAR EL EXTRACTO LIQUIDO Y CENTRIFUGARLO; SOMETER EL FLUIDO SOBRENADANTE A CROMATOGRAFIA DE AFINIDAD RECOGIENDO LA FRACCION PROTEINICA LA CUAL SE DIALIZA, LIOFILIZA Y REDISUELVE PARA SOMETERLA A OTRA CROMATOGRAFIA DE AFINIDAD PARA OBTENER LA PROTEINA DESEADA. LA NIGRINA B SE UTILIZA COMO INACTIVADOR DEL ACIDO RIBONUCLEICO E INHIBIDOR DE LA SINTESIS DE PROTEINAS.

column12: METHOD FOR OBTAINING RIBOSOMAL RNA RIBONUCLEASE WITH AN ACTIVITY INHIBITING THE PROTEINIC BIOSYNTHESIS FROM SEEDS OF CUCUMIS SATIVUS L., AND UTILIZATION THEREOF
column13: It has been possible to obtain from the seeds of the plant Cucumis sativus L. a protein which behaves like a catalytic inhibitor of the biosynthesis of proteins both of procaryotic and eucaryotic systems. The protein that we have named cusativin has been obtained and purified to electrophoretic homogeneity through the following steps: a) obtaining saline extracts from seeds b) obtaining acidifyed extracts from the prior extracts c) chromatography through S Sepharose Fast Flow (Pharmacia-LKB) d) ultrafiltration through membrane YM-10 of Amicon e) chromatography through Sephadex G 75 (Pharmacia-LKB) f) chromatography through CM Sepharose Fast Flow g) ultracentrifugation through membrane YM-10 of Amicon h) chromatography through Superdex 75-F.P.L.C. (Pharmacia-LKB) i) dialysis j) chromatography through Mono-S (F.P.L.C., Pharmacia-LKB) k) dialysis and lyophilization of the resultant protein.

Petroglaucin 1 has the following amino acid composition: Cys-23.2, Asp-19.1, Thr-18.5, Ser-22.8, Glu-26.5, Pro 19.4, Gly-23.7, Ala-17.7, Val-10.9, Met-1.7, Ile-13.2, Leu-17.7, Tyr-4.6, Phe-5.9, Lys-10.1, His-2.8, Arg-13.2. The process comprises: (a) extracting a lyophilisate of Petrocoptis glaucifolia (Lag.) Boiss, (b) filtering the liquid extract on a chromatographic bed, (c) subjecting the extracted fluid to ion exchange chromatography, (d) eluting the column with a solution of NaCl and NaH2PO4, (e) subjecting the eluted protein to ion exchange chromatography, (f) purifying the Petroglaucin 1 by ion exchange chromatography. Petroglaucin 1 is used as a ribonucleic acid inactivator and an inhibitor of protein synthesis.

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO DE OBTENCION DE UNA PROTEINA DE LA PLANTA CUCUMIS SATIVUS L., DENOMINADA CUSATIVINA, UTIL COMO INACTIVADOR DEL ACIDO RIBONUCLEICO E INHIBIDOR DE LA BIOSINTESIS DE PROTEINAS.
column13: COMPRENDE: (A) EXTRAER SEMILLAS SECAS DE CUCUMIS SATIVUS L. (B) FILTRAR, ACIDULAR EL EXTRACTO LIQUIDO, CENTRIFUGARLO Y CROMATOGRAFIARLO; (C) SOMETER EL FLUIDO OBTENIDO A CROMATOGRAFIA DE INTERCAMBIO IONICO; (D) ELUIR LA COLUMNA CON UNA SOLUCION DE NACL Y NAPOSI4 SCHSI2 SC; (E) SOMETER A ULTRAFILTRACION LA PROTEINA ELUIDA, A CROMATOGRAFIA Y A CROMATOGRAFIA DE INTERCAMBIO IONICO, OBTENIENDOSE FRACCIONES QUE SE CONCENTRAN POR ULTRAFILTRACION Y SE CROMTOGRAFIAN PARA DAR UNA FRACCION CONTENIENDO LA CUSATIVINA; (F) PURIFICAR LA CUSATIVINA MEDIANTE DIALISIS, CROMATOGRAFIA Y POSTERIOR LIOFILIZACION. APLICACION COMO INACTIVADOR DEL ACIDO RIBONUCLEICO E INHIBIDOR DE LA SINTESIS DE PROTEINAS CON POTENCIAL UTILIDAD EN LA TERAPIA DEL CANCER Y EL SIDA. DE LAS SEMILLAS DE LA PLANTA CUCUMIS SATIVUS L. SE HA OBTENIDO UNA PROTEINA QUE SE COMPORTA COMO INHIBIDOR CATALITICO DE LA BIOSINTESIS DE PROTEINAS TANTO DE SISTEMAS PROCARIONTES COMO EUCARIONTES. LA PROTEINA QUE DENOMINAMOS CUSATIVINA SE HA OBTENIDO Y PURIFICADO HASTA HOMOGENEIDAD ELECTROFORETICAMEDIANTE LOS SIGUIENTES PASOS: A) OBTENCION DE EXTRACTOS SALINOS A PARTIR DE SEMILLAS; B) OBTENCION DE EXTRACTOS ACIDIFICADOS A PARTIR DE LOS EXTRACTOS ANTERIORES; C) CROMATOGRAFIA A TRAVES DE S SEPHAROSE FAST FLOW (PHARMACIA-LKB); D) ULTRAFILTRACION A TRAVES DE MEMBRANA YM-10 DE AMICON; E) CROMATOGRAFIA A TRAVES DE SEPHADEX G 75 (PHARMACIA-LKB); F) CROMATOGRAFIA A TRAVES DE CM SEPHAROSE FAST FLOW; G) ULTRACENTRIFUGACION A TRAVES DE MEMBRANA YM-10 DE AMICON; H) CROMATOGRAFIA A TRAVES DE SUPERDEX 75-F.P.L.C. (PHARMACIA-LKB); I) DIALISIS; J) CROMATOGRAFIA A TRAVES DE MONO-S (F.P.L.C., PHARMACIALKB); K) DIALISIS Y LIOFILIZACION DE LA PROTEINA RESULTANTE.

Euserratin 4 has the following amino acid composition Cys- 0.8, Asp-35.8, Thr-15.8, Ser-20.0, Glu-20.6, Pro-9.8, Gly- 14.[illegible], Ala-11.6, Val-24.3, Met-1.6, Ile-15.4, Leu-29.9, Tyr-11.4, Phe-10.6, Lys-24.3, His-2.7, Arg-6.2. column12: Fiber optic position transducer with magnetostrictive material and position calibration process
column13: Fiber optic position transducer that includes a magnetic or electromagnetic element, one or more segments of magnetostrictive material, Fiber Bragg Grating Sensors, a rod of material that is impenetrable to magnetic fields, optical fiber. One or more of the sensors is fixed upon a segment of magnetostrictive material, which is fixed to a rod, and may only be displaced longitudinally. The Fiber Bragg Grating Sensors have different wave lengths and are made of the same optical fiber. The magnetic or electromagnetic element included may be made of NdFeB (Neodymium Iron Boron) or metal alloys of TbDyFe (Terbium, Dysprosium and Iron), such as TX, Terphenol-D and others. It is applied to a control flow valve in an oil well, and it also refers to the calibration process of the position of the transducer.

column12: Bauelement mit einer mikromechanischen Mikrofonstruktur und Verfahren zum Betreiben eines solchen Mikrofonbauelements
column13: Es wird ein Konzept für ein MEMS-Mikrofon vorgeschlagen, das auf einem relativ niedrigen Spannungsniveau betrieben werden kann und dennoch eine vergleichsweise hohe Empfindlichkeit aufweist. Neben einer mikromechanischen Mikrofonstruktur mit einer akustisch aktiven Membran, die als auslenkbare Elektrode eines Mikrofonkondensators (1) fungiert, und einem feststehenden akustisch durchlässigen Gegenelement, das als Gegenelektrode des Mikrofonkondensators (1) fungiert, umfasst das erfindungsgemäße Bauelement dazu - Mittel zum Anlegen eines hochfrequenten Taktsignals (2) an den Mikrofonkondensator (1) und zum Anlegen des invertierten Taktsignals (2') an einen einstellbaren aber akustisch nicht aktiven Kompensationskondensator (7), - einen integrierenden Operationsverstärker (3), der die Summe des Stromflusses durch den Mikrofonkondensator (1) und des Stromflusses durch den Kompensationskondensator (7) aufintegriert, - einen mit dem Taktsignal (2) synchronisierten Demodulator (4) für das Ausgangssignal des integrierenden Operationsverstärkers (3) und - einen Tiefpassfilter, um aus dem Ausgangssignal des Demodulators (4) ein den Kapazitätsänderungen des Mikrofonkondensators (1) entsprechendes Mikrofonsignal zu gewinnen.

column12: Component comprising a micromechanical microphone structure and method for operating said microphone component
column13: The invention relates to a concept for a MEMS microphone which can be operated at a relatively low voltage level and yet has a comparatively high sensitivity. The component according to the invention comprises a micromechanical microphone structure having an acoustically active diaphragm which serves as the deflectable electrode of a microphone condenser (1), and a stationary acoustically permeable counter-element which serves as the counter-electrode of the microphone condenser (1). In addition, the component comprises the following: means for applying a high-frequency clocked signal (2) to the microphone condenser (1) and for applying the inverted clocked signal (2') to an adjustable but acoustically inactive compensation condenser (7), an integrating operational amplifier (3) which integrates the sum of the current flow through the microphone condenser (1) and the current flow through the compensation condenser (7), a demodulator (4) for the output signal of the integrating operational amplifier (3), which demodulator is synchronized with the clocked signal (2), and a low-pass filter to use the output signal of the demodulator (4) to obtain a microphone signal which corresponds to the capacitance changes of the microphone condenser (1).

column12: TRANSDUCTOR DE POSICION A FIBRA OPTICA Y PROCESO DE CALIBRACION DELA POSICION DEL MISMO
column13: Transductor de posicion por fibra optica que comprende un elemento magnético o electromagnético, una o más piezas de material magnetoestrictivo sensores con redes de Bragg, barras de material no permeable a los campos magnéticos, fibra optica. Uno o más de los sensores mencionados está lijado a una pieza de material magnetoestrictivo que está lijada a una barra, y ésta se puede desplazar longitudinaImente. Los sensores con redes de Bragg tienen longitudes de onda diferentes y están en la misma fibra optica. El elemento magnético o electromagnético puede ser de neodimio, hierro, boro o por una aleacion metálica de Tb Dy Fe (terbio, disprosio e hierro), como el TX, o Terfenol-D u otros. La válvula de control de flujo se aplica a un pozo petrolero, también se refiere a un proceso de calibracion de la posicion del transductor.

column12: Component having a micromechanical microphone structure, and method for operating such a microphone component
column13: A concept is proposed for a MEMS microphone which may be operated at a relatively low voltage level and still have comparatively high sensitivity. The component according to the present invention includes a micromechanical microphone structure having an acoustically active diaphragm which functions as a deflectable electrode of a microphone capacitor ( 1 ), and a stationary acoustically permeable counterelement which functions as a counter electrode of the microphone capacitor ( 1 ). The component also includes means for applying a high-frequency clock signal ( 2 ) to the microphone capacitor ( 1 ) and for applying the inverted clock signal ( 2′ ) to an adjustable but acoustically inactive compensation capacitor ( 7 ), an integrating operational amplifier ( 3 ) which integrates the sum of the current flow through the microphone capacitor ( 1 ) and the current flow through the compensation capacitor ( 7 ), a demodulator ( 4 ) for the output signal of the integrating operational amplifier ( 3 ), the demodulator being synchronized with the clock signal ( 2 ), and a low-pass filter for obtaining a microphone signal which corresponds to the changes in capacitance of the microphone capacitor ( 1 ), based on the output signal of the demodulator ( 4 ).

column12: Mixed hydrophilic gels as controlled release vehicles or floating dispersants
column13: It consists of two hydrophilic polymers with gelling properties, giving rise to two gels, in which one of them is capable of interacting with the active ingredient (catching gel or gel A), at least modulating its release, and the other has the function of homogeneously dispersing the first gel, and ensuring the floatability and adhesion of the complex system in the gastric cavity, and may also intervene in the modulation of the active ingredient release (dilution gel or gel B). The product that is the object of the invention consists of the intimate mixture of the two hydrophilic gels that in turn consists of polysaccharides. One of the hydrophilic polysaccharides is agar, whereas the second can be selected from either alginate or chitosan.

column12: METHOD FOR OBTAINING RIBOSOMAL RNA RIBONUCLEASE WITH AN ACTIVITY INHIBITING THE PROTEINIC BIOSYNTHESIS FROM SEEDS OF CUCUMIS SATIVUS L., AND UTILIZATION THEREOF
column13: It has been possible to obtain from the seeds of the plant Cucumis sativus L. a protein which behaves like a catalytic inhibitor of the biosynthesis of proteins both of procaryotic and eucaryotic systems. The protein that we have named cusativin has been obtained and purified to electrophoretic homogeneity through the following steps: a) obtaining saline extracts from seeds; b) obtaining acidifyed extracts from the prior extracts; c) chromatography through S Sepharose Fast Flow (Pharmacia-LKB); d) ultrafiltration through membrane YM-10 of Amicon; e) chromatography through Sephadex G 75 (Pharmacia-LKB); f) chromatography through CM Sepharose Fast Flow; g) ultracentrifugation through membrane YM-10 of Amicon; h) chromatography through Superdex 75-F.P.L.C. (Pharmacia-LKB); i) dialysis; j) chromatography through Mono-S (F.P.L.C., Pharmacia-LKB); k) dialysis and lyophilization of the resultant protein.

column12: COMPONENT HAVING A MICROMECHANICAL MICROPHONE STRUCTURE, AND METHOD FOR OPERATING SUCH A MICROPHONE COMPONENT
column13: A concept is proposed for a MEMS microphone which may be operated at a relatively low voltage level and still have comparatively high sensitivity. The component according to the present invention includes a micromechanical microphone structure having an acoustically active diaphragm which functions as a deflectable electrode of a microphone capacitor ( 1 ), and a stationary acoustically permeable counterelement which functions as a counter electrode of the microphone capacitor ( 1 ). The component also includes means for applying a high-frequency clock signal ( 2 ) to the microphone capacitor ( 1 ) and for applying the inverted clock signal ( 2′ ) to an adjustable but acoustically inactive compensation capacitor ( 7 ), an integrating operational amplifier ( 3 ) which integrates the sum of the current flow through the microphone capacitor ( 1 ) and the current flow through the compensation capacitor ( 7 ), a demodulator ( 4 ) for the output signal of the integrating operational amplifier ( 3 ), the demodulator being synchronized with the clock signal ( 2 ), and a low-pass filter for obtaining a microphone signal which corresponds to the changes in capacitance of the microphone capacitor ( 1 ), based on the output signal of the demodulator ( 4 ).

column12: FIBER OPTIC POSITION TRANSDUCER WITH MAGNETOSTRICTIVE MATERIAL AND POSITION CALIBRATION PROCESS
column13: Fiber optic position transducer that includes a magnetic or electromagnetic element, one or more segments of magnetostrictive material, Fiber Bragg Grating Sensors, a rod of material that is impenetrable to magnetic fields, optical fiber. One or more of the sensors is fixed upon a segment of magnetostrictive material, which is fixed to a rod, and may only be displaced longitudinally. The Fiber Bragg Grating Sensors have different wavelengths and are made of the same optical fiber. The magnetic or electromagnetic element included may be made of NdFeB (Neodymium Iron Boron) or metal alloys of TbDyFe (Terbium, Dysprosium and Iron), such as TX, Terphenol-D and others. It is applied to a control flow valve in an oil well, and it also refers to the calibration process of the position of the transducer.

column12: transdutor de posição a fibra ótica com material magnetoestrictivo e processo de calibração da posição
column13: "TRANSDUTOR DE POSIçãO A FIBRA óPTICA COM MATERIAL MAGNETOESTRICTIVO E PROCESSO DE CALIBRAçãO DA POSIçãO". Transdutor de posição a fibra óptica que compreender um elemento magnético ou eletromagnético, uma ou mais peças de material magnetoestrictivo, sensores a rede de Bragg, haste de material não permeável a campos magnéticos, fibra óptica. Um ou mais dos ditos sensores está fixado a uma peça de material magnetoestrictivo, que está fixada na haste, e esta só pode se deslocar longitudinalmente. Os sensores a rede de Bragg têm comprimentos de onda diferentes e estão a mesma fibra óptica O elemento magnético ou eletromagnético compreende pode ser Neodímio Ferro Boro ou ligas metálicas de Tb Dy Fe (térbio, disprósio e ferro), como o TX, o Terfenol-D e outros. Aplica-se a válvula de controle de vazão em um poço de petróleo. também se refere ao processo de calibração da posição do transdutor.

column12: GAS-LIQUID-SOLID PRECIPITATION REACTOR
column13: The invention relates to a gas-liquid-solid precipitation reactor including scrubbing means (17, 18, 19, 20) associated with the lower outlet of a central tube (4) of an agitator (3), having an upper inlet through which a gas enters, said gas flowing through the central tube (4) and being released inside the lower part of the container (1) through a diffuser outlet (5), such as to bubble into a liquid reagent contained in the reactor. The aforementioned scrubbing means (17, 18, 19, 20) enable the simultaneous precipitation and discharge of solid particles contained in the gas when bubbled, without the reactor having to be stopped. The draining of the solids is facilitated with the use of a trap disk (24) on the internal base of the container (1), the upper face of which is provided with descending grooves (25) which direct the solids towards the base of the container (1) by means of agitation.

column12: REACTOR DE PRECIPITACION GAS-LIQUIDO-SOLIDO.
column13: Reactor de precipitación gas-líquido-sólido. Incorpora medios de limpieza (17, 18, 19, 20) asociados a la boca de salida inferior de un tubo central (4) de un agitador (3) por cuya entrada superior penetra un gas que atraviesa el tubo central (4) y desemboca inferiormente en el interior del depósito (1) a través de un difusor de salida (5) borboteando en un líquido reaccionante contenido en el reactor. Estos medios de limpieza (17, 18, 19, 20) permiten, de forma simultánea y sin necesidad de detener el reactor, la precipitación y salida de las partículas sólidas contenidas en el gas al tiempo que es borboteado. Asimismo se facilita el escurrido de los sólidos mediante un disco trampa (24) situado en el interior y sobre la base del depósito (1) que está dotado de unas acanaladuras descendentes (25) en su cara superior que dirige los sólidos hacia el fondo del depósito (1) por un movimiento de agitación.

column12: COMPONENT COMPRISING A MICROMECHANICAL MICROPHONE STRUCTURE AND METHOD FOR OPERATING SAID MICROPHONE COMPONENT
column13: The invention relates to a concept for a MEMS microphone which can be operated at a relatively low voltage level and yet has a comparatively high sensitivity. The component according to the invention comprises a micromechanical microphone structure having an acoustically active diaphragm which serves as the deflectable electrode of a microphone condenser (1), and a stationary acoustically permeable counter-element which serves as the counter-electrode of the microphone condenser (1). In addition, the component comprises the following: means for applying a high-frequency clocked signal (2) to the microphone condenser (1) and for applying the inverted clocked signal (2') to an adjustable but acoustically inactive compensation condenser (7), an integrating operational amplifier (3) which integrates the sum of the current flow through the microphone condenser (1) and the current flow through the compensation condenser (7), a demodulator (4) for the output signal of the integrating operational amplifier (3), which demodulator is synchronized with the clocked signal (2), and a low-pass filter to use the output signal of the demodulator (4) to obtain a microphone signal which corresponds to the capacitance changes of the microphone condenser (1).

column12: Protein Ebulin 1 from the plant Sambucus ebulus L., process for obtaining it and its use
column13: Protein Ebulin 1 from the plant Sambucus ebulus L., process for obtaining it and its use. Ebulin 1 is a ribosome-inactivator plant protein of the two A and B chain type with a relative molecular mass of 26,000 and 30,200 respectively. The process comprises extracting the plant Sambucus ebulus L., filtering the liquid extract and centrifuging it, subjecting the supernatant fluid to affinity chromatography, collecting the protein fraction which concentrates and subjecting it again to affinity chromatography to obtain the desired protein. Ebulin 1 is used as a ribonucleic acid inactivator and an inhibitor of protein synthesis.

column12: transdutor de pressão diferencial a fibra óptica
column13: "TRANSDUTOR DE PRESSãO DIFERENCIAL A FIBRA óPTICA". é descrito um transdutor (100, 200, 300, 400) de pressão diferencial a fibra óptica contendo redes de Bragg (118), dito transdutor sendo usado para medir a pressão diferencial em um Venturi instalado no interior de um duto (1) por onde se desloca um fluido como petróleo. O transdutor compreende um corpo (110, 230, 360, 410) de diferentes geometrias e um diafragma (2), pelo menos uma rede de Bragg (118) sendo afixada sobre cada uma das superfícies do mesmo. O diafragma (2) é colocado paralelo ou transversal ao corpo do transdutor (100, 200, 300, 400). O transdutor (200) é isolado do fluido de processo por selos mecânicos (201) flexíveis que transmitem a pressão até as superfícies do diafragma (2). O transdutor (300, 400) é dotado de duas microválvulas de alívio para efeitos de proteção do sensor ¢diafragmas (2)! em casos de sobre pressão.

column12: Fiber optics differential pressure transducer
column13: A fiber optics differential pressure transducer ( 100, 200, 300, 400 ) containing Bragg networks ( 118 ), said transducer being used to measure the differential pressure in a Venturi installed inside a pipe ( 1 ), through which a fluid like oil is displaced. The transducer comprises a body ( 110, 230, 360, 410 ) of different geometries and a diaphragm ( 2 ), at least one Bragg network ( 118 ) being attached on each of the surfaces of the same. The diaphragm ( 2 ) is placed parallel or transversal to the transducer's body ( 100, 200, 300, 400 ). The transducer ( 200 ) is isolated from the process fluid by flexible mechanical seals ( 201 ) which transmit the pressure up to surfaces of the diaphragm ( 2 ). The transducer ( 300, 400 ) is provided with two relief microvalves for the purpose of protecting the sensor [diaphragms ( 2 )] in overpressure events.

column12: TRANSDUCTOR DE POSICION A FIBRA OPTICA PARA VALVULA DE CONTROL DE CAUDAL EN POZOS INTELIGENTES
column13: Se describe un transductor de posicion (100) a fibra optica para válvula de control de caudal en pozos inteligentes, que comprende por lo menos dos células de carga (10) instrumentadas con sensores a redes de Bragg (FBG) y sustentadas por anillo (20S, 20b). La célula (10) está formada de un cuerpo cuadrangular (11), dotada de orificio central (12) y orificio (13S/13b) para entrada/salida y pasaje de una fibra optica (14) y pivotes (14S, 14b). La referida célula (10) mide el desplazamiento de un resorte utilizado en la válvula tipo sliding sleeve, rotativa o choke del sistema de completacion inteligente, siendo que el desplazamiento (abertura o cierre) de la válvula se monitorea a partir de la fuerza de restauracion en el resorte medido por la célula de carga (10) instrumentada. El transductor (100) está construido con dimensiones y geometría tales e manera de no presentar aristas y permitir la insercion del mismo en el espacio anular de una válvula tipo sliding sleeve, rotativa o choke e un sistema de produccion de petroleo. Además de ello, la construccion del transductor (100) es tal que permite que sea multiplexado a otros tipos de sensores de pozo, a través de la misma fibra optica.

column12: TRANSDUCTOR DE PRESION DIFERENCIAL A FIBRA OPTICA
column13: ? Transductor de presión diferencial a fibra óptica para medir a presión diferencial generada por un dispositivo tipo Venturi en pozos de petróleo, caracterizado porque comprende: a) un cuerpo principal (110) dotado de: - un agujero u orificio abierto (113); - de modo simétrico al referido agujero (113), un rebaje o bisel, (112) de ambos lados del referido cuerpo (110), estando dotado el rebaje (112) en el medio de un diafragma (2) para fijar por lo menos a una FBG, estando dicho cuerpo (110) conectado a: b) una tapa (115), dotada de rebaje (117) con extremos coincidentes y de la misma dimensión que el agujero abierto (113) y el rebaje (112), y un surco (116) para: i) abrigar el sello mecánico de vedación de la parte superior del referido transductor y ii) comunicar dicho agujero abierto (113) a una de las superficies del diafragma, (2) sometida a la acción de la presión, a otra superficie del diafragma (2) estando en contacto con otra toma de presión, el cuerpo (110) y la tapa (115) estando montados y fijados a un mandril de un ducto con auxilio de dispositivos de fijación a través de orificios (120), y donde: la fibra óptica (118) conteniendo por lo menos una FBG (118a) recorre agujeros (111a, 111b) en el cuerpo del transductor de tal forma que dicha FBG se encuentre exactamente sobre la parte central de las superficies del diafragma (2), el trayecto de la fibra comprendiendo el ingreso por un agujero (111a/111b) en una de las laterales del cuerpo (110) del transductor, paso a través del diafragma (2), siguiendo hasta el agujero abierto (113), circundar dicho agujero en un espiral hecho en las paredes del cuerpo (110); y volver a entrar en el cuerpo (110) en dirección a la otra superficie de diafragma (2) y finalmente salir del cuerpo (110), para ser conectada a otro transductor o al sistema de medición. <EMI FILE="05090935_1" ID="1" IMF=JPEG HE=50 WI=50 > SOLICITUDES DE PATENTES DE MODELO DE UTILIDADORDENADAS PUBLICAR EN FEBRERO DE 2007 IMPORTANTE:SOLICITUDES DE PATENTE DE MODELO DE UTILIDAD: A partir de la fecha de publicación de esta gaceta el solicitante cuenta con un plazo de tres (3) meses para pedir que se practique el examen de patentabilidad de la solicitud, anexando el recibo de pago de la tasa correspondiente a tal fin. De no procederse así la solicitud caerá en abandono (Arts. 85 y 44 de la Decisión 486).

column12: transdutor de posição a fibra óptica para válvula de controle de vazão em poços inteligentes
column13: "TRANSDUTOR DE POSIçãO A FIBRA óPTICA PARA VáLVULA DE CONTROLE DE VAZãO EM POçOS INTELIGENTES". é descrito um transdutor de posição (100) a fibra óptica para válvula de controle de vazão em poços inteligentes, que compreende pelo menos duas células de carga (10) instrumentadas com sensores a redes de Bragg (FBG) e sustentadas por anéis (20a, 20b). A célula (10) é formada de um corpo quadrangular (11), dotada de orifício central (12) e orifício (13a/13b) para entrada/saída e passagem de uma fibra óptica (14) e pinos (14a, 14b). A dita célula (10) mede o deslocamento de uma mola utilizada na válvula tipo sliding sleeve, rotativa ou choke do sistema de completação inteligente, o deslocamento (abertura ou fechamento) da válvula sendo monitorado a partir da força de restauração na mola medida pela célula de carga (10) instrumentada. O transdutor (100) é construído com dimensões e geometria tais de modo a não apresentar arestas e permitir a inserção do mesmo no espaço anular de uma válvula tipo sliding sleeve, rotativa ou choke de um sistema de produção de petróleo. Além disso, a construção do transdutor (100) é tal que permite que seja multiplexado a outros tipos de sensores de poço, através da mesma fibra óptica.

column12: Protein Nigrin b from the plant Sambucus nigra L., process for obtaining it and its use
column13: Protein Nigrin b from the plant Sambucus nigra L., process for obtaining it and its use. Nigrin b is a ribosome-inactivator plant protein of the two A and B chain type with a relative molecular mass of 26,600 and 31,600 respectively. The process comprises extracting the plant Sambucus nigra L., filtering the liquid extract and centrifuging it, subjecting the supernatant fluid to affinity chromatography, collecting the protein fraction which is dialysed, freeze dried and redissolved in order to subject it again to affinity chromatography to obtain the desired protein. Nigrin b is used as a ribonucleic acid inactivator and an inhibitor of protein synthesis.

column12: METHOD FOR IMPROVING THE OSTEOINTEGRATION OF OSSEOUS FIXING IMPLANTS
column13: The osteointegration of osseous fixing implants may be improved through a series of surface treatments. Said treatments comprise a cleaning and passivation process, tha application of a coating in the system Ca-P-H-O-C through the laser ablation technique and a sterilization process by irradiation. The flexibility of this method provides for the control of physico-chemical properties of the obtained surface in order to match said properties with those of the bone in which the implant will be placed.

column12: METODO DE MEJORA DE LA OSTEOINTEGRACION DE IMPLANTES DE FIJACION OSEA.
column13: LA OSTEOINTEGRACION DE IMPLANTES DE FIJACION OSEA PUEDE SER MEJORADA MEDIANTE UNA SERIE DE TRATAMIENTOS DE SU SUPERFICIE. ESTOS TRATAMIENTOS COMPRENDEN UN PROCESO DE LIMPIEZA Y PASIVADO, LA APLICACION DE UN RECUBRIMIENTO EN EL SISTEMA CA-P-H-O-C MEDIANTE LA TECNICA DE LA ABLACION LASER Y UN PROCESO DE ESTERILIZACION POR IRRADIACION. LA FLEXIBILIDAD DE ESTE METODO PERMITE CONTROLAR LAS PROPIEDADES FISICO-QUIMICAS DE LA SUPERFICIE RESULTANTE PUDIENDO SER ADAPTADAS A LAS DEL HUESO EN EL QUE VA A SER IMPLANTADO.

column12: Optical fiber position transducer for flow control valve in smart wells
column13: A fiber optics position transducer is described ( 100 ) for flow control valve in smart wells, which comprises at least two load cells ( 10 ) instrumented with Bragg (FGB) network sensors and supported by rings ( 20 a, 20 b ). The cell ( 10 ) is formed by a quadrangular body ( 11 ), provided with a central hole ( 12 ) and hole ( 13 a/ 13 b ) for inlet/outlet and passage of a fiber optic ( 14 ) and pins ( 14 a, 14 b ). Said cell ( 10 ) measures the displacement of a spring used in the sliding sleeve, rotating or choke type valve from the smart completion system, the displacement (opening or closing) of the valve being monitored from the restoration force in the spring measured by the instrumented load cell ( 10 ). The transducer ( 100 ) is built with dimensions and geometry so as not to present edges and allow the insertion of the same in the annular space of a sliding sleeve, rotating or choke type valve of an oil production system. In addition, the transducer's ( 100 ) construction is such that allows it to be multiplexed to other kinds of well sensors, through the same optical fiber.

column12: SISTEMA DESTINADO A DESTAPAR TOBERAS DE SOPLADO DE AIRE ENRIQUECIDO O GASES DE REACTORES O CONVERTIDORES DE FUSION EN LA PIROMETALURGIA DE LA INDUSTRIA MINERA
column13: DONDE EL METODO COMPRENDE: INYECTAR IMPACTOS DE AIRE DISCRETOS CON INTERVALOS DE TIEMPO REGULADOS A UNA PRESION ENTRE 70 Y 100 PSI Y A UNA VELOCIDAD ENTRE 195 Y 300 m/s, A TRAVES DE UNA TOBERA DE SOPLADO DE AIRE ENRIQUECIDO O GASES DE REACCION DE FORMA QUE LOS IMPACTOS PENETREN DENTRO DEL BANO EN FUNDICION PRESENTE EN LOS REACTORES O CONVERTIDORES, PARA PROVOCAR EL ROMPIMIENTO DE ACRECIONES OBSTRUCTIVAS QUE TAPAN EL FLUJO DEL AIRE O GAS A TRAVES DE LA TOBERA; Y FORMAR CON LOS IMPACTOS, PRODUCTO DEL ENFRIAMIENTO OCASIONADO POR LA PENETRACION DE LOS MISMOS, UNA ACRECION DIRIGIDA CON MATERIAL DEL BANO EN FUNDICION QUE SE SOLIDIFICA POR EFECTO DEL ENFRIAMIENTO, LOGRANDO QUE LA FORMACION DE ACRECION DIRIGIDA CONSTITUYA EL ALARGAMIENTO NATURAL DEL TUBO QUE COMPRENDE A LA TOBERA DESDE LA PARED INTERIOR DE LOS REACTORES O CONVERTIDORES, Y ASI PERMITIR QUE EL AIRE PENETRE MAS PROFUNDO EN DICHO BANO, A UNA DISTANCIA EN DONDE SE GENERA OLEAJE DE ESTE ULTIMO ALEJADO DE LA PARED CON MATERIAL REFRACTARIO DE LOS REACTORES O CONVERTIDORES EVITANDO EL DESGASTE DE DICHO REFRACTARIO, Y EL OLEAJE TIENDA A ELIMINAR LAS POSIBLES ACRECIONES OBSTRUCTIVAS QUE SE PUEDAN FORMAR. EL SISTEMA INCLUYE: a) UN RECEPTACULO CON CAPACIDAD PARA ALMACENAR AIRE COMPRIMIDO ENTRE 40 Y 60 LITROS Y A UNA PRESION ENTRE 70 Y 10 psi; b) UNA VALVULA DE PISTON PARA EVACUAR EL AIRE DE (a) A UNA VELOCIDAD ENTRE 263 Y 328 m/s; Y, c) UN MEDIDOR DE FLUJO, TAL COMO UN SENSOR OPTICO, EN LA TOBERA PARA OBSERVAR ALGUNA OBSTRUCCION

column12: TRANSDUCTOR DE PRESION DIFERENCIAL A FIBRA OPTICA
column13: Se describe un transductor (100, 200, 300, 400) de presion diferencial a fibra optica que contiene redes de Bragg (118); dicho transductor se utiliza para medir la presion diferencial en un Venturi instalado en el interior de un ducto, (1) por donde se desplaza un fluido como petroleo. El transductor comprende un cuerpo (110, 230, 360, 410) de diferentes geometrías y un diafragma (2), por lo menos una red de Bradd (118) que está fijada sobre cada una de las superficies del mismo. El diafragma (2) está colocado paralelo o transversal al cuerpo del transductor (100, 200, 300, 400). El transductor (200) está aislado del fluido de proceso por los sellos mecánicos (201) flexibles que transmiten la presion hasta las superficies del diafragma (2). El transductor (300, 400) está dotado de dos microválvulas de alivio para fines de proteccion del sensor [diafragmas (2)] en casos de exceso de presion.

column12: transdutor de posição a fibra óptica para válvula de controle de vazão em poços inteligentes
column13: "transdutor de posição a fibra óptica para válvula de controle de vazão em poços inteligentes". é descrito um transdutor de posição (100) a fibra óptica para válvula de controle de vazão em poços inteligentes, que compreende pelo menos duas células de carga (10) instrumentadas com sensores a redes de bragg (fbg) e sustentadas por anéis (20a, 20b). a célula (10) é formada de um corpo quadrangular (11), dotada de orifício central (12) e orifício (13a/13b) para entrada/saída e passagem de uma fibra óptica (14) e pinos (14a, 14b). a dita célula (10) mede o deslocamento de uma mola utilizada na válvula tipo sliding sleeve, rotativa ou choke do sistema de completação inteligente, o deslocamento (abertura ou fechamento) da válvula sendo monitorado a partir da força de restauração na mola medida pela célula de carga (10) instrumentada. o transdutor (100) é construído com dimensões e geometria tais de modo a não apresentar arestas e permitir a inserção do mesmo no espaço anular de uma válvula tipo sliding sleeve, rotativa ou choke de um sistema de produção de petróleo. além disso, a construção do transdutor (100) é tal que permite que seja multiplexado a outros tipos de sensores de poço, através da mesma fibra óptica.
